ng%20in%20church%20parking%20lots%20and%20coastal%20cities%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20could%20help%20solve%20the%20state's%20crisis%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20of%201709%20Broderick%20Street%2C%20the%20house%20depicted%20in%20the%20filming%20of%20the%20TV%20show%2C%20%26quot%3BFull%20House.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6532c5e396908fd7cdb42334%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22895%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESan%20Francisco%20Mayor%20London%20Breed%20celebrated%20new%20laws%20limiting%20the%20role%20of%20environmental%20regulations%20in%20restricting%20housing%20development.%3Cp%3EAvila%20Gonzalez%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ECalifornia%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20signed%20more%20than%2050%20bills%20this%20month%20designed%20to%20combat%20the%20housing%20crisis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EPro-housing%20advocates%20are%20celebrating%20this%20legislative%20session's%20wins.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20laws%20will%20legalize%20lots%20of%20new%20affordable%20housing%20construction%20and%20lift%20some%20burdensome%20regulations.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20is%20suffering%20from%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20most%20severe%20housing%20crises%2C%20fueled%20by%20a%20chronic%20shortage%20of%20places%20to%20live.%20The%20Golden%20State%20is%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-homelessness-crisis-homegrown-unhoused-are-californians-2023-6%5C%22%3Ehome%20to%20a%20third%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20country's%20unhoused%20population%20as%20lower-%20and%20middle-income%20residents%20struggle%20to%20afford%20homes%20all%20over%20the%20state.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20repeatedly%20promising%20to%20tackle%20the%20crisis%2C%20California%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20signed%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.ca.gov%2F2023%2F10%2F11%2Fgovernor-newsom-signs-package-to-streamline-housing-and-expand-tenant-protections-in-california%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2050%20housing%20bills%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20month.%20Pro-housing%20advocates%20say%20the%20patchwork%20of%20fixes%20are%20something%C2%A0of%20a%20mixed%20bag%2C%20but%20overall%20a%20strong%20move%20towards%20lifting%20burdensome%20regulations%20that%20make%20building%20unnecessarily%20costly%20or%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20wind%20is%20in%20our%20sails%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Ned%20Resnikoff%2C%20policy%20director%20at%20the%20pro-housing%20group%20California%20YIMBY%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BYes%20In%20My%20Backyard%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20really%20a%20lot%20of%20momentum%20behind%20efforts%20to%20solve%20the%20housing%20crisis%20in%20California.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20of%20the%20highlights%20from%20the%20historic%20slew%20of%20housing%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESpeeding%20up%20housing%20construction%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20major%20success%20of%20this%20legislative%20session%20are%20a%20few%20laws%20designed%20to%20loosen%20restrictions%20imposed%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopr.ca.gov%2Fceqa%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECalifornia's%20Environmental%20Quality%20Act%20(CEQA)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20broad%20set%20of%20regulations%C2%A0intended%20to%20protect%20environmental%20concerns%20but%20in%20recent%20years%20more%C2%A0notorious%20for%20slowing%20down%20or%20killing%20all%20kinds%20of%20housing%20development.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlmost%20anything%20under%20the%20sun%20can%20be%20considered%20an%20environmental%20impact%26quot%3B%20under%20CEQA%2C%20Chris%20Elmendorf%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20UC%20Davis%20law%20school%2C%20told%20Insider.%20And%20the%20unpredictability%20of%20CEQA's%20application%20adds%20significant%20costs%20to%20development.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20particularly%20notorious%20example%2C%20local%20opponents%20of%20a%20proposed%20student%20dorm%20building%20on%20the%20UC%20Berkeley%20campus%20drew%20the%20school%20into%20a%20prolonged%20legal%20battle%20over%20the%20construction%2C%20claiming%20the%20student%20residents%20would%20violate%20CEQA%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fopinion%2Fstory%2F2023-03-02%2Fcalifornia-uc-berkeley-ceqa-housing-environment%5C%22%3Ecreating%20noise%20pollution%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20state%20appellate%20court%20sided%20with%20the%20building's%20critics%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fsanfrancisco%2Fnews%2Fnewsom-signs-bill-to-clear-hurdles-for-student-housing-at-berkeleys-peoples-park%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20governor%20signed%20a%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20unanimously%20passed%20the%20legislature%2C%20specifically%20asserting%20that%20resident%20noise%20doesn't%20violate%20environmental%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20law%20the%20governor%20signed%20%E2%80%94%20Senate%20Bill%20423%20%E2%80%94%20extends%20and%20broadens%20a%20successful%202017%20law%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-affordable-housing-real-estate-ignores-community-input-opposition-2023-8%5C%22%3Ehas%20fast-tracked%20the%20construction%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20thousands%20of%20mostly%20affordable%20homes%20by%20requiring%20local%20governments%20to%20approve%20multi-unit%2C%20infill%20housing%20in%20existing%20residential%20neighborhoods.%20The%20new%20law%20%E2%80%94%20authored%20by%20one%20of%20California's%20most%20outspoken%20pro-housing%20lawmakers%2C%20State%20Sen.%20Scott%20Wiener%20%E2%80%94%20singles%20out%20San%20Francisco%2C%20which%20has%20struggled%20to%20meet%20its%20state-mandated%20housing%20construction%20requirements%20in%20part%20because%20of%20its%20lengthy%20approval%20process.%C2%A0The%20bill%20will%20require%20the%20city%20to%20undergo%20annual%20reviews%20and%20fast-track%20both%20market-rate%20and%20affordable%20housing%20construction.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20law%20%E2%80%94%20Assembly%20Bill%201633%20%E2%80%94%20will%20make%20it%20harder%20for%20cities%20to%20abuse%20CEQA%20to%20slow%20down%20or%20derail%20multi-unit%20infill%20housing%20construction%20if%20it%20complies%20with%20local%20requirements.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20first%20time%2C%20the%20legislature%20is%20really%20saying%2C%20we%20really%20just%20want%20this%20environmental%20review%20to%20be%20about%20the%20environment%20and%20not%20about%20stopping%20projects%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Elmendorf%2C%20who%20helped%20lawmakers%20craft%20AB%201633.%20The%20law%20affirms%20%26quot%3Bthe%20principle%20that%20if%20the%20project%20is%20compliant%20with%20the%20applicable%20rules%2C%20and%20on%20an%20infill%20location%20and%20reasonably%20dense%2C%20then%20the%20city%20can't%20use%20environmental%20review%20as%20a%20pretext%20to%20effectively%20deny%20projects%20they're%20not%20allowed%20to%20deny%20officially.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESan%20Francisco%20Mayor%20London%20Breed%20called%20the%20law%20%26quot%3Ba%20game%20changer%26quot%3B%20for%20her%20city%2C%20which%20has%20long%20been%20the%20poster%20child%20of%20housing%20crises.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20be%20an%20exciting%20time%20for%20housing%20development%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%26quot%3B%20Breed%20said%20during%20a%20panel%20at%20the%20Bloomberg%20CityLab%20conference%20in%20Washington%20on%20October%2019.%20%26quot%3BCEQA%20can't%20be%20abused%20like%20it%20has%20in%20the%20past%20because%20of%20changes%20to%20our%20state%20laws.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20law%20that's%20gotten%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0SB%204%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0will%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20non-profit%20colleges%20and%20universities%20and%20faith-based%20organizations%20to%20build%20affordable%20housing%20on%20land%20they%20already%20own.%20The%20bill%2C%20also%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BYes%20in%20God's%20Backyard%2C%26quot%3B%20would%20allow%20organizations%20to%20bypass%20certain%20environmental%20regulations%20and%20permitting%20rules%20to%20build%20homes%20in%20church%20parking%20lots%20and%20other%20underutilized%20or%20surplus%20land.%20UC%20Berkeley's%20Terner%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Innovation%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fternercenter.berkeley.edu%2Fresearch-and-policy%2Ffaith-based-and-college-land-housing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20there%20are%20more%20than%20170%2C000%20acres%20of%20land%20that%20could%20be%20put%20to%20use%20under%20SB%204.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResnikoff%20noted%20that%20religious%20organizations%20are%20especially%20well-positioned%20to%20provide%20housing%20for%20low-income%20and%20even%20unhoused%20community%20members.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20this%20whole%20network%20of%20mission-driven%20organizations%20across%20the%20entire%20state%2C%20many%20of%20which%20would%20be%20quite%20eager%20and%20willing%20to%20minister%20to%20the%20most%20housing-burdened%20in%20their%20areas%2C%20and%20this%20is%20a%20way%20to%20provide%20that%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ten%20new%20homes%20in%20Long%20Beach%2C%20California%20at%20the%20intersection%20of%20Pine%20Avenue%20and%2014th%20Street.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6532d3f496908fd7cdb440d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22842%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETen%20homes%20in%20Long%20Beach%20constructed%20by%20Habitat%20for%20Humanity%20of%20Greater%20Los%20Angeles.%3Cp%3EBrittany%20Murray%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ESome%20disappointments%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Elmendorf%20thinks%20the%20overall%20progress%20made%20on%20housing%20policy%20this%20legislative%20session%20was%20positive%2C%20he%20lamented%20the%20failure%20of%20a%20pair%20of%20bills%20that%20would've%20allowed%20more%20density%20in%20single-family%20neighborhoods%20by%20legalizing%20lot%20subdivisions.%20The%20bills%20died%20in%20the%20legislature%2C%20which%20Elmendorf%20said%20speaks%20to%20lawmakers'%20continued%20reticence%20to%20stand%20up%20to%20homeowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20housing%20advocates%20are%20also%20disappointed%20that%20Newsom%20vetoed%20a%20bill%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0AB%20309%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0to%20create%20%26quot%3Bsocial%20housing%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0on%20government-owned%20land.%20The%20proposal%2C%20authored%20by%20South%20Bay%20Assemblymember%20Alex%20Lee%2C%20would%20have%20piloted%20mixed-income%20housing%20developments%20on%20public%20land.%20Rather%20than%20restricting%20the%20homes%20to%20only%20very%20low-income%20residents%2C%20as%20most%20public%20housing%20does%2C%20residents%20from%20all%20socio-economic%20backgrounds%20would%20spend%20no%20more%20than%2030%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20rent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20like%20how%20roads%2C%20and%20libraries%2C%20and%20schools%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0no%20matter%20how%20rich%20or%20poor%20you%20are%2C%20you%20still%20are%20entitled%20to%20go%20check%20out%20a%20book%20or%20go%20to%20send%20your%20kids%20to%20public%20school.%20That's%20the%20same%20thing%20with%20housing%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20said%20he%20explicitly%20modeled%20the%20proposal%20off%20social%20housing%20programs%20in%20Vienna%2C%20Austria%20and%20Singapore%20that%20have%20long%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F05%2F23%2Fmagazine%2Fvienna-social-housing.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecelebrated%20by%20housing%20advocates%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20and%20around%20the%20world.%20%26quot%3BIf%20a%20modest%20Central%20European%20power%20and%20a%20modest%20trading%20commercial%20power%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%20can%20come%20successfully%20with%20a%20huge%20track%20record%20of%20social%20housing%2C%20why%20can't%20the%20most%20prosperous%20state%20and%20the%20most%20prosperous%20nation%20in%20the%20history%20of%20mankind%20be%20able%20to%20do%20that%20too%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20passed%20the%20legislature%2C%20but%20Newsom%20vetoed%20it%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.ca.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAB-309-Veto.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earguing%20in%20a%20lengthy%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20state%20doesn't%20have%20the%20budget%20capacity%20for%20the%20project.%20Resnikoff%2C%20whose%20organization%20endorsed%20the%20effort%2C%20noted%20that%20the%20state's%20current%20fiscal%20conditions%20make%20it%20very%20hard%20to%20pass%20housing%20policy%20that%20requires%20funding.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdvocates%20are%20quick%20to%20point%20out%20that%20California%20housing%20policy%20has%20impacts%20far%20beyond%20its%20borders.%20The%20state's%20housing%20policies%20have%20already%20inspired%20copycat%20efforts%20across%20the%20country.%20Resnikoff%20said%20he%20saw%20lots%20of%20similarities%20between%20New%20York%20City%20Mayor%20Eric%20Adams'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-city-real-estate-prices-housing-apartments-eric-adams-2023-9%5C%22%3Enewly-proposed%20housing%20reforms%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20include%20legalizing%20building%20small%20secondary%20housing%20units%20on%20one's%20property%20and%20boosting%20density%20in%20commercial%20corridors.%20How%20effectively%20California%20deals%20with%20its%20housing%20affordability%20issues%20also%20directly%20impacts%20other%20states'%20housing%20markets.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcalmatters.org%2Fcalifornia-divide%2F2020%2F01%2Fnot-the-golden-state-anymore-middle-and-low-income-people-leaving-california%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emigration%20of%20California%20residents%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20places%20from%20Texas%20to%20Oregon%C2%A0%20has%20put%20additional%20pressure%20on%20those%20states%20to%20provide%20even%20more%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-apartment-rent-housing-shortage-crisis-solution-laws-prices-decline-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697971081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6532c5efbe9edfa8eda65368%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-apartment-rent-housing-shortage-crisis-solution-laws-prices-decline-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Pro-housing%20advocates%20are%20celebrating%20new%20housing%20laws%20addressing%20burdensome%20environmental%20regulations%20and%20opening%20up%20land%20for%20affordable%20homes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-apartment-rent-housing-shortage-crisis-solution-laws-prices-decline-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22120%20incubator%20babies%20at%20risk%20after%20Israel%20cuts%20Gaza%20fuel%3A%20UN%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697971063000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104627587%2Cimgsize-488675.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2F120-incubator-babies-at-risk-after-israel-cuts-gaza-fuel-un%2Farticleshow%2F104627246.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104627246.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20lives%20of%20at%20least%20120%20newborn%20babies%20on%20incubators%20in%20war-torn%20Gaza's%20hospitals%20are%20at%20risk%20as%20fuel%20runs%