3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20year%2C%20humans%20worldwide%20eat%20over%20100%20billion%20bananas%2C%20most%20of%20which%20are%20a%20type%20called%20the%20Cavendish.%20But%20perhaps%20not%20for%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20fungal%20disease%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcavendish-banana-may-go-extinct-disease-2021-6%5C%22%3Ethreatens%20to%20wipe%20Cavendish%20bananas%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0off%20the%20face%20of%20the%20Earth.%20Some%20scientists%20are%20genetically%20modifying%20the%20fruit%20to%20be%20more%20resistant%20to%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20best%20solution%20to%20the%20problem%2C%20some%20argue%2C%20is%20for%20farmers%20to%20completely%20overhaul%20banana%20production%20and%20stop%20growing%20only%20one%20variety%20of%20fruit%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20Cavendish%20bananas%20dominate%20the%20global%20market%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20over%201%2C000%20varieties%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fripe-unripe-bananas-which-are-better-for-you-2018-7%5C%22%3Ebananas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20about%2047%25%20that%20humans%20eat%20are%20Cavendish%20bananas%20(Musa%20acuminata).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222415%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Banana%20plantations%20at%20La%20Palma%2C%20Canary%20Islands%2C%20Spain.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525cc4f68f1d46f52addf5d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221240%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20banana%20plantations%20grow%20just%20one%20type%20banana%20variety.%3Cp%3Etrabantos%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECavendish%20dominates%20the%20global%20banana%20market%20for%20several%20reasons.%20One%2C%20it's%20resistant%20to%20some%20of%20the%20major%20banana-killing%20diseases%3B%20two%2C%20it%20has%20a%20long%20shelf%20life%3B%20and%20three%2C%20farmers%20can%20typically%20grow%20more%20Cavendish%20bananas%20than%20other%20varieties%20on%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20of%20all%20these%20reasons%2C%20Cavendish%20becomes%20a%20very%20practical%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20journalist%20Dan%20Koeppel%2C%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BBanana%3A%20The%20Fate%20of%20the%20Fruit%20That%20Changed%20the%20World%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Cavendish%20is%20under%20threat%20from%20a%20fungus%20that%20infects%20the%20plant.%20The%20infection%20is%20called%20Panama%20Disease%20(Fusarium%20wilt)%20tropical%20race%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETR4%20infection%20starts%20in%20the%20banana%20tree's%20roots%20and%20then%20spreads%2C%20ultimately%20disabling%20the%20plant's%20ability%20to%20absorb%20water%20or%20conduct%20photosynthesis.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20tree%20dies%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Close%20up%20of%20unripe%2C%20green%20bananas%20growing%20on%20a%20tree.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525cd0855f52b01b35bc37d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPanama%20disease%20has%20been%20killing%20bananas%20for%20well%20over%20a%20century.%3Cp%3EFajri%20Ramadhan%20%2F%20500px%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EPanama%20disease%20is%20a%20serial%20banana%20killer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20happening%20to%20Cavendish%20bananas%20has%20happened%20before%20to%20another%20popular%20banana%20variety%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbanana-fruit-changes-history-2016-2%3FIR%3DT%5C%22%3EGros%20Michel%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGros%20Michel%20was%20the%20%26quot%3Bmain%20export%20banana%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20last%20century%2C%26quot%3B%20James%20Dale%2C%20a%20professor%20and%20leader%20of%20the%20banana%20biotechnology%20program%20at%20Queensland%20University%20of%20Technology%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20predecessor%20to%20TR4%2C%20called%20tropical%20race%201%2C%20began%20infecting%20bananas%20in%201876.%20By%20the%201950s%2C%20it%20had%20completely%20decimated%20Gros%20Michel%20farms%2C%20forcing%20banana%20producers%20across%20the%20globe%20to%20look%20for%20a%20new%20variety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Black%20and%20white%20photo%20of%20workers%20sorting%20Cavendish%20bananas%20at%20a%20farm%20in%201982.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525cd746561dd877e76d22d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22678%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBy%201982%2C%20Cavendish%20bananas%20had%20all%20but%20replaced%20the%20Gros%20Michel%20variety.%3Cp%3ERobert%20Nickelsberg%20%2F%20Contributor%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20following%20years%2C%20%26quot%3BCavendish%20became%20the%20leading%20export%20banana%20replacing%20Gros%20Michel%20because%20it%20was%20immune%20to%20TR1%2C%26quot%3B%20Dale%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201997%2C%20scientists%20detected%20a%20new%20strain%20(TR4)%20near%20Darwin%2C%20Australia%2C%20that%20infected%20Cavendish.%20By%202015%2C%20it%20had%20spread%20to%20the%20banana%20farms%20in%20Queensland%2C%20the%20largest%20banana-producing%20state%20in%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20then%20it%20has%20spread%20to%20India%20and%20China%2C%20the%20world's%20largest%20producers%20of%20bananas.%20It%20has%20also%20spread%20to%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20Africa%20and%20very%20recently%20was%20found%20in%20South%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20Dale%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20scientists%20are%20trying%20to%20save%20the%20Cavendish%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20plant%20pathologists%20don't%20believe%20that%20the%20Cavendish%20banana%20will%20meet%20the%20same%20fate%20as%20Gros%20Michel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20disease%20moves%20slowly%2C%20so%20we%20have%20at%20least%20a%20decade%20before%20the%20impact%20is%20drastic%2C%26quot%3B%20Dale%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20many%20scientists%20are%20working%20on%20TR4-resistant%20Cavendish%20or%20a%20resistant%20replacement%20for%20Cavendish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fungi%20Fusarium%20which%20produce%20mycotoxins%20in%20cereal%20crops%20including%20bananas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525cec76561dd877e76d362%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20TR4%20infects%20banana%20roots%2C%20ultimately%20killing%20the%20plant.%3Cp%3EDr_Microbe%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Dale%20and%20his%20colleagues%20have%20developed%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.qut.edu.au%2Fnews%3Fid%3D186769%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egenetically%20modified%20Cavendish%20called%20QCAV-4%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20they%20said%20is%20highly%20resistant%20to%20TR4.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20research%20group%20led%20by%20scientists%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%20is%20exploring%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cam.ac.uk%2Fresearch%2Fnews%2Fnew-grafting-technique-could-combat-the-disease-threatening-cavendish-bananas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrafting%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20possible%20solution.%20Grafting%20tissue%20from%20one%20plant%20onto%20another%20can%20alter%20certain%20characteristics%20of%20that%20plant%2C%20like%20making%20it%20more%20resistant%20to%20disease%2C%20per%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20team%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.promusa.org%2FGCTCV-119%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETaiwan%20Banana%20Research%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20attempting%20a%20form%20of%20natural%20selection.%20The%20team%20takes%20Cavendish%20seedlings%20and%20exposes%20them%20to%20TR4.%20The%20small%20portion%20of%20seedlings%20that%20fair%20best%20then%20go%20onto%20additional%20experiments%20to%20ultimately%20help%20the%20Cavendish%20evolve%20to%20become%20resistant%20to%20TR4%2C%20absent%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fgmo-pros-and-cons%5C%22%3Egenetic%20modification%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%20with%20certainty%20that%20there%20will%20be%20a%20solution%20before%20the%20export%20market%20for%20Cavendish%20is%20severely%20affected%2C%26quot%3B%20Dale%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20banana%20experts%20argue%20that%20such%20solutions%20won't%20work%20long%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThere's%20no%20single%20solution%20to%20the%20problem%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20true%20that%20there%20is%20some%20resistance%2C%20but%20I'd%20say%20right%20now%2C%20nobody%20is%20even%20close%20to%20solving%20the%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Koeppel%20told%20Insider%2C%20adding%20%26quot%3BThe%20answer%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20end%20of%20monoculture.%20The%20answer%20is%20variety.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20suggests%20that%20replacing%20the%20current%20banana%20cultivar%20with%20a%20new%20disease-resistant%20variety%20is%20a%20short-term%20solution%20because%20the%20fungi%20can%20also%20come%20up%20with%20a%20new%20and%20more%20powerful%20strain%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bananas%20at%20a%20market%20in%20Thailand.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525d5856561dd877e76dded%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22681%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFood%20markets%20of%20the%20future%20could%20carry%20as%20many%20varieties%20of%20bananas%20as%20apples.%3Cp%3EDEA%20%2F%20G.%20COZZI%20%2F%20Contributor%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20solution%20is%20to%20mass%20produce%20and%20sell%20more%20than%20one%20banana%20variety%20because%20the%20more%20genetically%20diverse%20bananas%20are%2C%20the%20less%20likely%20they'll%20be%20susceptible%20to%20diseases%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20it%20would%20also%20reduce%20the%20dependence%20of%20humans%20on%20one%20type%20of%20banana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BApples%20are%20a%20huge%20example%20of%20this.%20Today%20If%20I%20go%20to%20any%20supermarket%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20will%20find%20between%20five%20and%2030%20apple%20varieties%2C%26quot%3B%20Koeppel%20said.%20%26quot%3BApple%20growers%20are%20going%20nuts%20trying%20to%20introduce%20new%20varieties%20naturally%20as%20well%20as%20through%20hybridization%2C%20and%20genetic%20modification.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20reduces%20the%20risk%20of%20disease%2C%20offers%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.in%2Fscience%2Fnews%2Fthis-new-variety-of-apple-has-a-10-million-hype-machine-behind-it-160and-farmers-are-hoping-it-can-save-washingtons-apple-industry%2Farticleshow%2F73278319.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20variety%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20customers%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foldest-apple-orchard-in-america-apple-picking-season-2021-9%3FIR%3DT%5C%22%3Eapple%20growers%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20still%20making%20a%20lot%20more%20money%20because%20of%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20with%20bananas%2C%20Koeppel%20said%2C%20is%20that%20there%20are%20far%20fewer%20varieties%2C%20and%20they're%20all%20cheap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20add%20variety%2C%20the%20investment%20will%20pay%20off%20very%20quickly%20because%20suddenly%20some%20people%20will%20pay%20%244%20a%20pound%20for%20certain%20bananas%2C%26quot%3B%20Koeppel%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDale%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20isn't%20so%20sure.%20%26quot%3BPrice%20is%20the%20driver%2C%26quot%3B%20of%20banana%20sales%20in%20his%20country%20Australia.%20He%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BMost%20people%20will%20purchase%20Cavendish%20because%20it%20is%20cheap.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntroducing%20a%20wider%20variety%20of%20bananas%20would%20not%20only%20drive%20up%20costs%20but%20would%20also%20require%20a%20major%20overhaul%20in%20how%20we%20transport%20bananas%20%E2%80%94%20since%20you%20can't%20just%20store%20them%20in%20freezers%20for%20long%20periods%20like%20apples%2C%20Dale%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20export%20market%20is%20dependent%20on%20harvesting%20Cavendish%20green%20and%20then%20inducing%20ripening%20by%20ethylene%20gassing.%20This%20is%20done%20during%20transport%20and%20is%20very%20tightly%20controlled%20and%20tailored%20to%20Cavendish%2C%26quot%3B%20Dale%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20there%20were%20multiple%20varieties%20of%20bananas%20exported%20then%20it%20is%20likely%20that%20each%20would%20need%20specific%20defined%20ripening%20conditions.%20And%20of%20course%20the%20price%20would%20increase.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20seems%20to%20be%20no%20single%20solution%20to%20the%20problem%20that's%20working%2C%20so%20far.%20Perhaps%20history%20is%20bound%20to%20repeat%20itself%20and%20Cavendish%20will%20no%20longer%20be%20the%20banana%20of%20choice%20in%20the%20near%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbananas-going-extinct-gros-michel-cavendish-disease-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697966221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525ced655f52b01b35bc51a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbananas-going-extinct-gros-michel-cavendish-disease-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Are%20bananas%20going%20extinct%3F%20The%20Gros%20Michel%20did%2C%20and%20the%20Cavendish%20variety%20is%20battling%20disease.%20Here's%20how%20scientists%20are%20trying%20to%20save%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Rupendra%20Brahambhatt)%22%2C%22enga