.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMathias%20D%C3%B6pfner%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Insider's%20parent%20company%2C%20Axel%20Springer%2C%20recently%20met%20with%20Microsoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%20for%20a%20wide-ranging%20interview.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interview%20took%20place%20in%20Berlin%20at%20Axel%20Springer's%20headquarters%2C%20where%20Nadella%20was%20honored%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axelspringer.com%2Fen%2Fax-press-release%2Fhe-rewrote-the-code-for-a-new-era-satya-nadella-honored-with-axel-springer-award%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20Axel%20Springer%20Award%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20recognizes%20%26quot%3Boutstanding%20personalities%20who%20demonstrate%20an%20exceptional%20talent%20for%20innovation%2C%20create%20and%20transform%20markets%2C%20shape%20culture%2C%20and%20also%20face%20their%20social%20responsibility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EYou%20can%20read%20a%20transcript%20of%20D%C3%B6pfner's%20conversation%20with%20Nadella%20below.%20The%20interview%20has%20been%20lightly%20edited%20for%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESatya%2C%20the%20world%20knows%20you're%20a%20big%20cricket%20fan.%20Cricket%20is%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20mystery%20for%20Germans.%20But%20we%20do%20realize%20it's%20a%20great%20time%20for%20cricket%20just%20now.%20The%20cricket%20world%20cup%20is%20taking%20place%20in%20India%2C%20and%20there's%20talk%20of%20the%20Olympic%20Games%202036%20being%20in%20India%2C%20too.%20Which%20is%20very%20exciting%20for%20cricket%20fans%20because%20it's%20scheduled%20to%20become%20an%20Olympic%20discipline%20again%20in%202028.%20Could%20you%20tell%20us%20a%20little%20about%20personal%20fascination%20with%20the%20sport%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20Indian%20and%20a%20South%20Asian%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20more%20than%20a%20religion.%20For%20all%20of%20us%2C%20it's%20what%20we%20grew%20up%20with.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20it%20you%20have%20learned%20from%20cricket%20about%20leadership%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20one%20time%20we%20were%20playing%20a%20league%20match%20in%20the%20city%20I%20grew%20up%20in%20Hyderabad%20and%20there%20was%20a%20player%20from%20Australia%20playing%20in%20that%20league%20match.%20We%20were%20all%20sitting%20there%20admiring%20this%20guy%20and%20what%20he%20was%20doing%20on%20the%20field.%20And%20I%20distinctly%20remember%20my%20coach%20standing%20behind%20me%20and%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20don't%20just%20admire%20from%20a%20distance%2C%20go%20and%20compete!%26quot%3B%20For%20me%2C%20that%20was%20a%20great%20way%20of%20saying%3A%20when%20you're%20on%20the%20field%2C%20how%20do%20you%20go%20in%20there%20and%20give%20it%20your%20all.%20Learn%20from%20your%20competition%2C%20but%20don't%20be%20in%20awe%20of%20your%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20incident%20I%20remember%20is%20a%20game%20where%20I%20was%20playing%20under%20one%20of%20the%20captains.%20One%20of%20our%20players%20was%20very%20good%2C%20but%20for%20some%20reason%20or%20another%20he%20was%20not%20happy%20with%20the%20decisions%20the%20captain%20was%20making%20on%20the%20field.%20And%20he%20was%20dropping%20these%20catches%20on%20purpose%20just%20to%20make%20a%20point.%20That%20really%20influenced%20me%20a%20lot%3A%20this%20one%20player%20brought%20the%20entire%20morale%20of%20the%20team%20down%20on%20purpose%20just%20because%20he%20was%20not%20happy%20about%20things.%20And%20I%20do%20think%20that%2C%20from%20time%20to%20time%20you%20get%20into%20situations%20in%20the%20workplace%20where%20you%20have%20one%20person%20who%20is%20not%20really%20bought%20in%2C%20and%20that's%20something%20you%20really%20have%20to%20act%20on.%20The%20situation%20where%20I%20learned%20the%20most%20was%20when%2C%20one%20day%2C%20I%20was%20having%20a%20very%20bad%20streak%2C%20and%20my%20captain%20took%20me%20off.%20He%20came%20in%20himself%20and%20got%20a%20breakthrough%20or%20a%20wicket.%20But%20then%20he%20gave%20the%20ball%20back%20to%20me%20and%2C%20interestingly%2C%20I%20went%20on%20to%20get%20a%20bunch%20of%20wickets%20in%20that%20match.%20I%20asked%20him%20why%20he%20did%20that%2C%20let%20me%20play%20again%20even%20though%20I%20was%20having%20a%20bad%20day.%20He%20said%20to%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20need%20you%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20season%2C%20so%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20break%20your%20confidence.%26quot%3B%20And%20this%20was%20high%20school%20cricket%2C%20and%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20God%2C%20this%20guy%20is%20an%20enlightened%20captain.%26quot%3B%20So%2C%20in%20some%20sense%2C%20if%20you're%20leading%20a%20team%2C%20you%20don't%20just%20want%20that%20team%20for%20one%20time%2C%20you%20need%20them%20for%20the%20duration.%20When%20I%20look%20back%2C%20there%20are%20lots%20of%20incidents%20that%20have%20given%20me%20a%20bunch%20of%20lessons%20to%20take%20away.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221971%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Josh%20Inglis%20of%20Australia%20Cricket%20team.%20Watch%20Australia%20at%20bat%20against%20India%20in%20the%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%20with%20these%20free%20live%20streams.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651eea229f7ca8b2bbda7eaf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221478%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20cricket%20player%20photographed%20during%20a%20match.%3Cp%3EPankaj%20Nangia%20(Stringe)%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20way%20you%20became%20the%20CEO%20of%20Microsoft%20is%20quite%20a%20story%20in%20itself.%20You%20were%20typologically%20pretty%20much%20the%20anti-Steve%20Ballmer%20and%20not%20the%20favorite%20at%20the%20beginning.%20And%20you%20were%20quite%20a%20sharp%20contrast%20culturally.%20You%20became%20CEO%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Binternal%20stranger.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20that's%20a%20great%20way%20of%20describing%20it%20actually.%20Having%20grown%20up%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20first%20during%20Bill's%20tenure%2C%20and%20then%20Steve's%20tenure%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20I%20ever%20got%20up%20in%20the%20morning%20and%20thought%20that%20someday%20Microsoft%20would%20have%20neither%20Bill%20nor%20Steve.%20And%20quite%20frankly%2C%20when%20Steve%20announced%20that%20he%20was%20going%20to%20leave%2C%20it%20was%20a%20real%20shock%20to%20me.%20I%20remember%20quite%20distinctly%20one%20of%20the%20board%20members%20asking%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20want%20to%20be%20the%20CEO%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BOnly%20if%20you%20want%20me%20to%20be%20the%20CEO.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%20I%20told%20this%20to%20Steve%2C%20because%20the%20board%20members%20were%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20know%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20be%20the%20CEO%2C%20you%20really%20need%20to%20want%20to%20be%20the%20CEO.%26quot%3B%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BGod%2C%20I've%20not%20thought%20about%20it%2C%20I%20don't%20know.%26quot%3B%20Steve%20was%20very%20interesting.%20He%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20too%20late%20to%20change%2C%20so%20just%20be%20yourself%20and%20see%20what%20happens.%26quot%3B%20In%20retrospect%2C%20I%20think%20the%20board%20did%20what%20they%20had%20to%20do%20in%20the%20succession%20process.%20They%20looked%20broadly%20on%20the%20outside%2C%20and%20they%20looked%20deep%20on%20the%20inside%2C%20and%20then%20they%20made%20their%20decision.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20is%20a%20story%20that%20you%20were%20asked%20what%20you%20would%20do%20if%20you%20found%20a%20child%20screaming%20in%20the%20street%20during%20an%20interview%20before%20joining%20Microsoft%20in%201992.%20And%20you%20just%20said%20you%20would%20call%20911.%20Is%20that%20story%20true%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20this%20very%20distinctly%20because%20there%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20programming%20questions%20throughout%20the%20day.%20I%20was%20having%20to%20code%20all%20the%20time%2C%20and%20I%20was%20exhausted.%20Then%20this%20last%20guy's%20question%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20would%20you%20do%20if%20you%20were%20crossing%20the%20road%20and%20a%20child%20fell%20down%20and%20was%20crying.%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI'd%20go%20to%20the%20nearest%20phone%20booth%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20before%20cell%20phones%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20would%20call%20911.%26quot%3B%20He%20got%20up%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20time%20for%20you%20to%20leave.%20When%20a%20child%20is%20crying%2C%20you%20pick%20them%20up%20and%20give%20them%20a%20hug%20and%20you%20need%20to%20have%20empathy.%26quot%3B%20I%20was%20sure%20I'd%20never%20get%20a%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20you%20a%20very%20rational%20person%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20developed%20more%20understanding%20and%20empathy%20over%20the%20years%20for%20the%20world%20and%20people%20around%20me.%20If%20you%20train%20and%20grow%20as%20an%20engineer%2C%20like%20I%20did%2C%20then%20you%20think%20your%20goal%20is%20to%20be%20more%20rational.%20But%20in%20reality%2C%20as%20Herbert%20Simon%20frames%20it%2C%20we%20are%20only%20rational%20to%20an%20extent.%20Therefore%2C%20I%20think%20there's%20no%20harm%20in%20being%20able%20to%20mix%20rationality%20with%20your%20own%20understanding%20and%20empathy%20for%20the%20people%20in%20the%20world%20around%20you.%20Life's%20experience%20teaches%20us%20that%20none%20of%20us%20can%20get%20by%20without%20the%20kindness%20of%20the%20people%20around%20us.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWere%20your%20parents%20very%20ambitious%20for%20you%3F%20One%20story%20has%20it%20that%20your%20father%20put%20a%20poster%20of%20Karl%20Marx%20in%20your%20room%2C%20because%20he%20wanted%20you%20to%20become%20a%20philosopher%2C%20whereas%20your%20mother%20put%20a%20poster%20of%20Lakshmi%2C%20the%20goddess%20of%20beauty%20and%20love%20and%20wealth.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20that's%20right.%20Interestingly%2C%20both%20my%20parents%20were%20successful%20in%20their%20own%20way.%20My%20dad%20was%20a%20civil%20servant%2C%20and%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20a%20Marxist%20economist.%20And%20my%20mother%20was%20a%20professor%20of%20Sanskrit.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20your%20father%20was%20a%20Marxist%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20say%2C%20he%20was%20a%20left-of-center%20civil%20servant.%20One%20interesting%20thing%20he%20told%20me%20was%20that%20being%20too%20doctrinaire%2C%20too%20dogmatic%2C%20is%20a%20mistake.%20He%20was%20happy%20to%20go%20to%20Hayek%20or%20Marx%2C%20as%20long%20as%20it%20met%20his%20needs.%20He%20was%20practical%20in%20that%20sense.%20India%20was%20a%20newly%20independent%20country%20and%2C%20as%20a%20civil%20servant%2C%20he%20cared%20mostly%20about%20the%20development%20of%20the%20country.%20And%20that%20influenced%20me%20a%20lot.%20To%20get%20back%20to%20your%20question%2C%20yes%2C%20they%20were%20ambitious%20for%20me.%20They%20wanted%20me%20to%20have%20the%20room%20to%20learn%20and%20grow%20and%20not%20just%20follow%20what%20was%20happening.%20When%20I%20look%20back%20at%20it%2C%20as%20a%20middle-class%20kid%20growing%20up%20in%20India%2C%20they%20gave%20me%20a%20lot%20more%20room%20to%20develop%20my%20own%20interests%2C%20follow%20my%20own%20passions%2C%20and%20to%20develop%20my%20own%20point%20of%20view%20on%20topics%2C%20without%20being%20indoctrinated%20on%20anything.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Axel%20Springer%20CEO%20Mathias%20D%C3%B6pfner%20interviews%20Microsoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6533d81596908fd7cdb49579%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221217%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAxel%20Springer%20CEO%20Mathias%20D%C3%B6pfner%20interviews%20Microsoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%20at%20the%202023%20Axel%20Springer%20Award%20event.%3Cp%3EAxel%20Springer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWould%20you%20say%20you%20had%20a%20happy%20childhood%20altogether%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOh%2C%20yes%2C%20absolutely.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20you%20always%20feel%20loved%2C%20unconditionally%20loved%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbsolutely.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20think%20that%20unconditional%20love%20is%20an%20important%20factor%20for%20future%20personality%20development%2C%20because%20you%20feel%20that%20certainty%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20a%20lot%20about%20that.%20If%20you%20have%20a%20loving%20environment%20at%20home%2C%20that%20gives%20you%20confidence%20to%20tackle%20the%20world%20and%20the%20challenges%20that%20it%20poses.%20It%20makes%20a%20huge%20difference.%20I%20do%20think%20that%20unconditional%20love%20and%20support%20are%20massive%20parts%20of%20our%20development.%20If%20you%20grow%20up%20in%20a%20home%20with%20parents%20who%20are%20invested%20in%20your%20success%2C%20not%20so%20much%20in%20the%20outcome%2C%20but%20more%20in%20giving%20you%20the%20best%20shots%2C%20then%20that's%20the%20greatest%20break%20you%20can%20have%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELast%20year%20your%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Eson%20passed%20away%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0at%20the%20age%20of%2026%2C%20having%20been%20born%20with%20cerebral%20palsy.%20To%20what%20degree%20has%20that%20also%20influenced%20you%2C%20your%20definition%20of%20family%2C%20of%20unconditional%20love%20and%20leadership%20style%3F%20Is%20any%20of%20that%20related%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes.%20You%20know%2C%20my%20son%20Zain's%20birth%20made%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20grow%20up%20very%20quickly.%20And%20quite%20frankly%2C%20it%20was%20one%20place%20where%20I%20learned%20a%20ton%20from%20my%20wife.%20I%20was%2029%2C%20and%20she%20was%2027%2C%20and%20if%20you%20had%20asked%20me%20the%20day%20before%20he%20was%20born%20what%20we%20were%20most%20worried%20about%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20my%20wife%20going%20back%20to%20work%2C%20where%20we%20could%20get%20childcare%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20Then%20he%20was%20born%2C%20and%20our%20life%20changed%20a%20great%20deal.%20Even%20though%20it%20was%20hard%20for%20me%20to%20accept%2C%20it%20was%20very%20clear%20that%20his%20life%20was%20going%20to%20be%20challenging.%20And%20so%2C%20we%20really%20needed%20to%20buckle%20up%20and%20help%20him%20as%20best%20as%20we%20could.%20For%20the%20longest%20time%20I%20suffered%20from%20it%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20did%20this%20happen%20to%20me%3F%20And%20why%20is%20this%20now%20upsetting%20all%20the%20plans%20and%20ideas%20I%20had%20about%20my%20life%3F%26quot%3B%20Then%20I%20looked%20at%20my%20wife%2C%20and%20she%20was%20getting%20up%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20and%20she%20gave%20up%20her%20job%20as%20an%20architect%2C%20and%20she%20was%20going%20to%20every%20therapy%20possible%20throughout%20the%20Seattle%20area.%20She%20was%20completely%20dedicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20that%20nothing%20had%20happened%20to%20me%2C%20something%20happened%20to%20my%20son%2C%20and%20as%20a%20parent%20I%20needed%20to%20be%20there%20to%20support%20him.%20It%20took%20me%20years%3B%20it%20wasn't%20like%20an%20instant%20epiphany.%20But%20it%20was%20a%20process%20in%20which%20I%20grew%20a%20lot%2C%20I%20would%20say.%20And%20I%20know%20it%20changed%20me%20as%20a%20leader%2C%20and%20it%20changed%20me%20fundamentally%20as%20a%20human%20being.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221842%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Microsoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%20with%20the%20word%20%26quot%3BMicrosoft%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20Microsoft%20logo%20displayed%20behind%20him%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a6f2b36075be0019c2dbfd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221382%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESatya%20Nadella%20took%20over%20as%20Microsoft%20CEO%20from%20Steve%20Ballmer%20in%202014.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWould%20you%20say%20that%20it%20made%20you%20more%20thankful%2C%20perhaps%20even%20more%20humble%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20I%20think%20it%20just%20helped%20me%20grow%20my%20empathy%2C%20understanding%20that%20I%20was%20able%20to%20see%20the%20world%20through%20my%20son's%20eyes%20as%20opposed%20to%20my%20own.%20That%2C%20I%20think%2C%20started%20having%20a%20real%20impact%20on%20how%20I%20showed%20up%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20how%20I%20showed%20up%20as%20a%20husband%2C%20how%20I%20showed%20up%20as%20a%20friend%2C%20a%20son%2C%20a%20manager%2C%20a%20colleague.%20It%20fundamentally%20changed%20me%20where%20I%20could%20relate%20to%20when%20someone%20was%20going%20through%20something.%20When%20somebody%20says%20something%2C%20I%20don't%20just%20look%20at%20it%20purely%20from%20my%20point%20of%20view%20but%20try%20to%20understand%20where%20they're%20coming%20from%20and%20what's%20happening%20in%20their%20life.%20And%2C%20quite%20frankly%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20flexibility%20and%20leeway%20given%20to%20me%20by%20some%20of%20the%20leaders%20I%20worked%20for%20when%20my%20son%20was%20young%20really%20influenced%20me.%20I%20was%20a%20nobody%2C%20just%20a%20first-level%20manager%20at%20the%20company%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20what%20I%20experienced%20back%20then%20shaped%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20be.%20It%20was%20a%20very%20defining%20moment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeing%20a%20leader%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20empathy%20and%20determination%20to%20change%20Microsoft's%20culture%20from%20a%20rather%20rectangular%20and%20masculine%20into%20a%20more%20open%20and%20understanding%20one%2C%20and%20focusing%20more%20on%20soft%20skills%20rather%20than%20performance%20KPIs%20is%20one%20of%20your%20greatest%20successes%20and%20critical%20achievements%20as%20CEO.%20You%20grew%20the%20company%20valuation%20from%20a%20valuation%20of%20%24400%20billion%20to%20roughly%20%242.5%20trillion%2C%20and%20analysts%20are%20optimistic%20it%20will%20grow%20further.%20What%2C%20in%20your%20mind%2C%20is%20the%20most%20important%20cultural%20decision%20you%20have%20made%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmpathy%20is%20often%20seen%20as%20a%20soft%20skill%2C%20but%20I%20actually%20think%20it's%20a%20hard%20one.%20And%20that%20has%20to%20do%20with%20design%20thinking.%20I've%20always%20thought%20of%20design%20thinking%20as%20the%20ability%20to%20meet%20unmet%2C%20unarticulated%20needs.%20And%20so%2C%20having%20that%20ability%20to%20absorb%20what%20is%20happening%2C%20and%20then%20conceive%20innovation%2C%20comes%20from%2C%20in%20some%20sense%2C%20having%20deep%20empathy%20for%20the%20jobs%20to%20be%20done.%20This%20is%20why%20I%20believe%20it's%20a%20very%20important%20%E2%80%93%20and%20perhaps%20the%20only%20sustainable%20%E2%80%93%20design%20and%20innovation%20skill%20for%20success.%20But%2C%20coming%20back%20to%20your%20question%20on%20culture%3A%20by%20the%20late%2090s%2C%20Microsoft%20had%20achieved%20tremendous%20success.%20In%20fact%2C%20we%20became%20the%20company%20with%20the%20largest%20market%20cap.%20When%20that%20happened%2C%20people%20were%20walking%20around%20campus%20thinking%20they%20were%20God's%20gift%20to%20innovation.%20I%20like%20to%20frame%20this%20as%20us%20becoming%20know-it-alls.%20Later%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20this%20was%20not%20the%20case%20and%20that%20we%20needed%20a%20really%20important%20change%20from%20being%20know-it-alls%20to%20becoming%20learn-it-alls.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuckily%2C%20I%20had%20read%20this%20book%20called%20%26quot%3BMindset%26quot%3B%20by%20Carol%20Dweck%20a%20few%20years%20before%20I%20became%20CEO.%20My%20wife%20had%20introduced%20me%20to%20it%20in%20the%20context%20of%20my%20children's%20education.%20Carol%20Dweck%20talks%20about%20%26quot%3Bgrowth%20mindset.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20school%20setting%2C%20you%20can%20really%20encourage%20kids%20to%20have%20a%20growth%20mindset%20by%20helping%20them%20learn%20from%20the%20mistakes%20they%20made.%20When%20they're%20not