20decision%20that%20you%20regret%20in%20retrospect%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20I%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20talk%20about%20%E2%80%93%20and%20one%20of%20the%20most%20difficult%20decisions%20I%20made%20when%20I%20became%20CEO%20%E2%80%94was%20our%20exit%20of%20what%20I'll%20call%20the%20mobile%20phone%20as%20defined%20then.%20In%20retrospect%2C%20I%20think%20there%20could%20have%20been%20ways%20we%20could%20have%20made%20it%20work%20by%20perhaps%20reinventing%20the%20category%20of%20computing%20between%20PCs%2C%20tablets%2C%20and%20phones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20the%20best%20decision%20you've%20made%20so%20far%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20best%20decision%20is%20the%20operating%20model%20of%20the%20company.%20I%20realized%20I%20was%20taking%20over%20from%20a%20founder.%20And%20I%20couldn't%20run%20the%20company%20like%20a%20founder.%20We%20needed%20to%20run%20the%20company%20as%20a%20team%20of%20senior%20leaders%20who%20are%20accountable%20to%20the%20entire%20company.%20And%20even%20the%20senior%20leaders%20cannot%20be%20isolated%2C%20they%20need%20to%20be%20grounded.%20So%20we%20found%20a%20way%20to%20be%20able%20to%20work%20together.%20There%20used%20to%20be%20this%20characterization%2C%20this%20caricature%20of%20Microsoft%20as%20a%20bunch%20of%20silos%20%E2%80%93%20which%20I%20thought%20was%20unfair.%20We%20were%20able%20to%20debunk%20that%20by%20showing%20that%20we%20are%20one%20team%20working%20together%2C%20flexible%20in%20our%20own%20ways%20but%20very%20fixed%20on%20our%20outcome%20goals.%20And%20that%2C%20I%20think%2C%20was%20probably%20the%20most%20important%20thing.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20that%20controversial%20at%20the%20beginning%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20new.%20We%20didn't%20grow%20up%20with%20that.%20When%20I%20look%20back%2C%20Bill%20and%20Steve%20had%20many%20management%20teams%20that%20came%20and%20went.%20They%20were%20the%20constants%2C%20and%20they%20maintained%20consistency%20in%20their%20heads%2C%20and%20they%20could%20manage%20the%20business%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20needed%20great%20players%20at%20all%20times.%20They%20didn't%20need%20a%20team.%20Whereas%2C%20we%20needed%20to%20evolve%20to%20become%20a%20management%20team.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%2C%20the%20Activision%20Blizzard%20deal%20has%20finally%20been%20approved.%20Why%20is%20that%20so%20important%3F%2065%20billion%20is%20quite%20a%20price.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%2C%20but%20we're%20really%20excited%20about%20it.%20For%20us%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20things%20that%20go%20all%20the%20way%20back%20for%20us%20as%20a%20company.%20Gaming%20is%20one%2C%20right%3F%20When%20I%20think%20about%20Microsoft%2C%20I%20think%20of%20perhaps%20developer%20tools%2C%20proprietary%20software%2C%20and%20gaming.%20Those%20are%20three%20things%20that%20we've%20done%20from%20the%20very%20beginning.%20And%20so%2C%20to%20us%2C%20gaming%20is%20the%20one%20place%20where%20we%20think%20we%20have%20a%20real%20contribution%20to%20make%20in%20consumer%20markets.%20If%20I%20look%20at%20it%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20people%20allocate%20to%20gaming%20is%20going%20up%20and%20Gen%20Z%20is%20going%20to%20do%20more%20of%20that.%20The%20way%20games%20are%20made%2C%20the%20way%20the%20games%20are%20delivered%2C%20is%20changing%20radically.%20Whether%20it's%20mobile%2C%20or%20consoles%2C%20or%20PCs%2C%20or%20even%20the%20cloud.%20So%2C%20we're%20looking%20forward%20to%20really%20doubling%20down%20both%20as%20a%20game%20producer%20and%20a%20publisher.%20Now%20we'll%20be%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20game%20publishers%20and%20also%20as%20a%20company%20that's%20building%20platforms%20for%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221777%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22activision%20blizzard%20logo%20stage%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e497f5bd98a600197bad42%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5