adigm%2C%20then%20you%20could%20lose%20it%20all.%20The%20technical%20shift%20is%20one%20aspect.%20The%20other%20is%20the%20business%20model%2C%20and%20you%20can't%20really%20expect%20the%20business%20model%20of%20the%20future%20to%20be%20exactly%20the%20same%20as%20the%20business%20model%20of%20the%20past.%20Cloud%20was%20a%20great%20example.%20We%20had%20a%20fantastic%20business%20model%20with%20servers%2C%20and%20cloud%20was%20completely%20disruptive.%20That%20I%20think%20is%20the%20thing%20to%20watch%20out%20for.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20open%20source%20an%20existential%20risk%20for%20Microsoft%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20thought%20so%20in%20the%20early%20days.%20And%20it%20was.%20In%20some%20sense%2C%20open%20source%20was%20the%20biggest%20governor%2C%20or%20rate%20limiter%20on%20what%20happens%20in%20proprietary%20software.%20I%20grew%20up%20in%20fact%2C%20doing%20a%20lot%20of%20interrupts%20of%20Windows%20and%20Windows%20NT%20on%20our%20backend%20servers%20with%20Unix%20and%20Linux.%20And%20I%20then%20realized%20that%20the%20more%20we%20interoperate%20with%20open%20source%2C%20the%20better%20it%20is%20for%20our%20business.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20are%20you%20saying%20we%20should%20embrace%20it%3F%20Has%20that%20always%20been%20your%20spirit%3F%20That%2C%20if%20you%20see%20a%20threat%20or%20a%20danger%20or%20a%20challenge%2C%20then%20you%20tend%20to%20embrace%20it%20instead%20of%20fighting%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20I%20take%20the%20non-zero-sum%20way%20of%20approaching%20things.%20So%2C%20whenever%20I%20face%20challenges%2C%20I'm%20very%20conscious%20that%2C%20in%20business%2C%20sometimes%20we%20all%20go%20to%20everything%20being%20zero-sum%2C%20and%20in%20reality%2C%20there%20are%20very%20few%20things%20that%20are%20zero-sum.%20One%20of%20the%20things%20I%20have%20learned%2C%20at%20least%20as%20a%20business%20strategist%2C%20is%20to%20be%20very%20crisp%20about%20what%20those%20zero-sum%20battles%20are%2C%20and%20then%20to%20really%20look%20for%20non-zero-sum%20constructs%20everywhere.%20And%20so%20open%20source%20is%20one%20such%20thing.%20In%20fact%2C%20we%20are%20the%20largest%20contributor%20to%20open%20source%20today.%20And%20obviously%2C%20GitHub%20is%20the%20home%20for%20open%20source.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJeff%20Bezos%20got%20famous%20with%20the%20phrase%2C%20%26quot%3BOne%20day%20Amazon%20will%20go%20bankrupt.%26quot%3B%20So%20far%20in%20business%20history%2C%20all%20companies%20went%20bankrupt%20sooner%20or%20later.%20Is%20that%20also%20true%20for%20Microsoft%2C%20or%20is%20Microsoft%20too%20big%20to%20fail%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20there's%20no%20God-given%20right%20that%20businesses%20should%20just%20keep%20going.%20They%20should%20only%20keep%20going%20if%20they're%20serving%20some%20social%20purpose%2C%20for%20example%2C%20producing%20something%20that%20is%20innovative%20and%20interesting.%20Corporations%20should%20be%20grounded%20in%20whether%20they%20are%20doing%20anything%20relevant%20for%20the%20world%20or%20not.%20Longevity%20is%20not%20a%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20long%20do%20you%20want%20to%20remain%20CEO%3F%20And%20what%20are%20the%20goals%20that%20you%20have%20set%20for%20yourself%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20I'm%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20so%20many%20things%20that%20I'm%20not%20able%20to%20think%20about%20what%20will%20come%20next.%20I'm%20close%20to%20being%20a%20CEO%20for%20ten%20years%20and%20a%20big%20believer%20in%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20institutional%20strength%20you%20build%20is%20only%20evident%20after%20you're%20gone.%20When%20I%20look%20at%20what%20Steve%20left%2C%20it%20was%20a%20very%20strong%20company%20that%20I%20could%20pick%20up%20and%20do%20what%20I%20needed%20to%20do%20with.%20And%20so%2C%20if%20my%20successor%20is%20very%20successful%2C%20then%20that%20would%20indicate%20that%20I%20have%20done%20something%20useful.%20I'm%20mindful%20of%20how%20to%20build%20that%20institutional%20strength%20to%20reinvent%20oneself.%20And%20that's%20the%20trickiest%20part.%20It's%20not%20about%20continuing%20some%20tradition%2C%20but%20more%20about%20being%20able%20to%20have%20the%20strength%20to%20reinvent%20yourself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWould%20it%20be%20fair%20to%20say%20that%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20you%20realize%20you're%20unable%20to%20reinvent%20yourself%2C%20you%20should%20retire%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20good%20point.%20Yes%2C%20I%20think%20everyone%20reaches%20a%20point%20where%20it's%20time%20to%20have%20things%20refreshed.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20have%20potential%20successors%20in%20the%20company%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbsolutely.%20I%20think%20there's%20lots%20of%20people%20out%20there%20and%20I'm%20confident%20the%20board%20will%20do%20their%20job%20when%20the%20time%20comes.%20We've%20been%20very%20conscious%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20it's%20not%20about%20me%2C%20not%20about%20just%20one%20person%20and%20one%20culture%20or%20personality.%20It's%20about%20a%20company%20with%20many%20leaders%2C%20who%20all%20are%20very%2C%20very%20capable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20you%20as%20a%20CEO%2C%20but%20also%20for%20the%20time%20after%20this%20role%2C%20what%20could%20and%20should%20you%20give%20back%20to%20society%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20my%20wife%20and%20I%2C%20having%20lived%20through%20the%20experience%20with%20our%20son%2C%20are%20very%20thankful%20for%20all%20the%20institutions%20and%20people%20and%20the%20community%20that%20supported%20us%20through%20some%20very%20trying%20times.%20And%20so%2C%20one%20of%20the%20things%20that%20we're%20very%2C%20very%20passionate%20about%2C%20is%20what%20we%20can%20do%20for%20families%20with%20special-needs%20children.%20We%20work%20very%20extensively%20with%20the%20Children's%20Hospital%20in%20Seattle%20and%20many%20of%20the%20other%20institutions%20that%20were%20very%20supportive.%20Being%20a%20working-class%20parent%20with%20a%20special-needs%20kid%20makes%20it%20impossible%20for%20you%20to%20be%20able%20to%20hold%20down%20your%20job%20and%20take%20care%20of%20your%20child.%20That's%20one%20of%20the%20hardest%20challenges%2C%20I%20think.%20Another%20area%20is%20first-generation%20education%2C%20because%20education%20is%20the%20best%20tool%20for%20social%20mobility.%20At%20the%20university%20I%20went%20to%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Wisconsin%20in%20Milwaukee%2C%20we're%20very%20focused%20on%20helping%20first-generation%20kids%20get%20STEM%20degrees%20so%20they%20can%20have%20better%20job%20opportunities.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222265%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Microsoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%20testified%20in%20federal%20court%20Thursday%2C%20as%20the%20FTC%20sues%20to%20block%20its%20%2470%20billion%20acquisition%20of%20Activision%20Blizzard%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c3f639cf07780019669b43%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221699%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMicrosoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%20testified%20in%20federal%20court%20Thursday%2C%20as%20the%20FTC%20sues%20to%20block%20its%20%2470%20billion%20acquisition%20of%20Activision%20Blizzard%3Cp%3EAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet's%20talk%20about%20business%20ethics.%20Milton%20Friedman%20once%20famously%20said%3A%20%26quot%3Bthe%20business%20of%20business%20is%20business.%26quot%3B%20I%20think%20current%20conflicts%20show%20this%20is%20not%20true%2C%20or%20at%20least%20not%20true%20any%20longer.%20What%20learnings%20can%20we%20draw%20from%20that%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20things%20you%20brought%20up%2C%20both%20of%20which%20I%20think%20are%20worth%20talking%20about.%20One%20is%2C%20is%20the%20business%20of%20business%20just%20business%3F%20I%20actually%20do%20believe%20so.%20The%20reason%20I%20say%20that%2C%20fundamentally%2C%20is%20because%20sometimes%20business%20leaders%20can%20get%20very%2C%20very%20confused.%20The%20social%20purpose%20of%20a%20company%20is%20to%20be%20able%20to%20create%20useful%20products%20that%20generate%20profits%20for%20their%20shareholders.%20And%20so%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20Milton%20Friedman%2C%20if%20you%20remember%2C%20his%20entire%20rationale%20came%20because%20a%20lot%20of%20CEOs%20and%20corporations%20were%20going%20haywire%2C%20and%20not%20being%20disciplined%20in%20how%20they%20allocated%20capital%20and%20performed%20for%20their%20shareholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20being%20said%2C%20we%20live%20in%20the%20real%20world%2C%20which%20is%20kind%20of%20your%20point.%20Therefore%2C%20you%20cannot%2C%20as%20a%20business%20leader%2C%20somehow%20think%20that%20the%20job%20of%20business%20is%20just%20business%20and%20ignore%20the%20geopolitics%20of%20the%20world.%20In%20the%20long%20run%2C%20it%20will%20come%20back%20to%20bite%20you.%20If%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20supply%20chain%20that%20works%20or%20that%20is%20broken%20because%20of%20geopolitics%2C%20then%20that%20is%20your%20business.%20So%20therefore%2C%20regarding%20your%20point%2C%20the%20way%20I%20look%20at%20it%2C%20even%20your%20book%20says%2C%20hey%2C%20as%20a%20business%20leader%2C%20you%20need%20to%20be%20grounded%20on%20which%20countries%20you%20can%20do%20business%20in.%20There%20might%20be%20places%20where%20you%20cannot%20do%20business%20because%20there's%20a%20conflict%20of%20values%20between%20countries.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20cannot%20tolerate%20double%20standards.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20tightening%20our%20ESG%20criteria%20every%20day%2C%20while%20at%20the%20same%20time%20moving%20large%20parts%20of%20our%20business%20to%20countries%20where%20homosexuality%20is%20illegal%20or%20where%20a%20woman%20can%20be%20stoned%20to%20death%20for%20adultery.%20It%20just%20doesn't%20go%20together.%20We%20have%20to%20find%20a%20middle%20ground.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20right.%20And%20it's%20an%20interesting%20question%3A%20What%20is%20our%20role%20as%20a%20multinational%20corporation%3F%20And%20do%20we%20have%20a%20set%20of%20values%20that%20are%20universal%3F%20And%20how%20do%20they%20deal%20with%20cultural%20differences%3F%20And%20how%20do%20you%20not%20try%20to%20supersede%20the%20democratic%20process%3F%20The%20way%20I%20approach%20it%20as%20a%20multinational%20company%2C%20or%20rather%20an%20American%20company%2C%20is%20that%20we%20have%20to%20take%20the%20core%20values%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20yet%20meet%20the%20world%20where%20it%20is.%20You%20have%20to%20understand%20that%20there%20are%20going%20to%20be%20massive%20cultural%20differences.%20You%20have%20a%20set%20of%20values%20that%20you%20live%20by%2C%20but%20you%2C%20as%20a%20multinational%20corporation%2C%20can't%20dictate%20what%20people%20in%20any%20country%20choose%20or%20don't%20choose%20to%20believe.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20you%20can%20still%20live%20your%20values%20as%20a%20company%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that's%20an%20important%20distinction.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20your%20prediction%20concerning%20our%20business%20relationship%20with%20China%2C%20the%20second%20biggest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%2C%20ten%20years%20from%20now%3F%20Is%20there%20going%20to%20be%20a%20unilateral%20decoupling%20by%20the%20US%20from%20China%3F%20Is%20it%20going%20to%20be%20a%20bigger%20alliance%20of%20solidarity%20between%20democracies%20in%20derisking%20from%20China%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20more%20likely%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20do%20business%20as%20usual%20with%20China%2C%20and%20everything%20is%20going%20to%20be%20fine%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wish%20I%20could%20predict%20that%20future%2C%20but%20that%20is%20a%20question%20for%20the%20world.%20There's%20a%20part%20of%20me%20that%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BGod%2C%20what's%20up%3F%26quot%3B%20Today%2C%20decoupling%20clearly%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20conventional%20wisdom.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlmost%20one%20of%20the%20very%20few%20non-partisan%20topics%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExactly.%20Whether%20in%20DC%20or%20Beijing%2C%20it%20seems%20that%20both%20sides%20have%20voted%2C%20and%20decoupling%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20only%20option.%20I%20don't%20think%20we%20have%20even%20a%20political%20theory%20for%20it%2C%20where%20we%20have%20two%20very%20different%20powers%2C%20one%20a%20Western%20Power%2C%20one%20an%20Eastern%20power%3B%20one%20an%20authoritarian%20communist%20state%2C%20and%20the%20other%20a%20democracy%2C%20with%20two%20completely%20different%20political%20economies.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20we%20see%20a%20duopoly%20of%20sorts%2C%20with%20two%20AI%20world%20powers%20competing%20against%20each%20other%20in%20a%20new%20AI%20arms%20race%3F%20Or%20do%20you%20think%20it%20is%20imaginable%20that%20we%20will%20one%20day%20have%20a%20kind%20of%20unilateral%20AI%20governance%20and%20infrastructure%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20do%20think%20some%20level%20of%20global%20governance%20will%20be%20required.%20The%20way%20I%20look%20at%20it%2C%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20competition%20is%20what%20will%20be%20there.%20But%20if%20there%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20successful%2C%20let's%20call%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bregime%20of%20control%26quot%3B%20over%20AI%2C%20then%20we%20will%20need%20some%20global%20cooperation%20like%20the%20IAEA.%20You%20know%2C%20what%20we've%20done%20in%20the%20atomic%20sphere%20might%20be%20the%20moral%20equivalent%20in%20AI%20where%20China%20also%20needs%20to%20be%20at%20the%20table.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20why%20would%20China%20respect%20and%20accept%20a%20different%20set%20of%20rules%20or%20a%20governance%20that%20is%20also%20based%20on%20ethical%20limits%20that%20may%20not%20apply%20in%20any%20way%20to%20Chinese%20standards%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20kind%20of%20the%20issue.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20China%20ultimately%20needs%20to%20decide%20what%20its%20long-term%20interests%20are.%20And%20whether%20they%20are%20really%20that%20different%20from%20the%20long-term%20interests%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20we%20have%20to%20bring%20them%20to%20the%20table%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20to.%20We%20have%20real%20world%20concerns%20today.%20In%20the%20United%20States%20and%20in%20Europe%2C%20we're%20talking%20about%20really%20practical%20issues%20like%20bias%2C%20disinformation%2C%20or%20the%20economy%20and%20jobs.%20These%20are%20all%20things%20we%20will%20have%20to%20tackle%20in%20a%20real-world%20way%2C%20so%20that%20AI%20is%20actually%20helpful%2C%20not%20harmful.%20Those%20are%20the%20things%20we%20are%20dealing%20with%20today.%20And%20then%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20there%20is%20existential%20risk%20of%20a%20runaway%20AI.%20China%20should%20care%20about%20that.%20Even%20if%20it%20thinks%20about%20the%20first%20real-world%20issues%20in%20a%20different%20way%2C%20because%20of%20their%20political%20system%2C%20it%20should%20care%20about%20the%20runaway%20AI%20problem%2C%20too.%20So%2C%20I%20think%20figuring%20out%20at%20least%20some%20common%20ground%20on%20governance%20is%20going%20to%20be%20helpful.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EElon%20Musk%20said%20he's%20potentially%20more%20afraid%20about%20AI%20than%20about%20nukes.%20Do%20you%20agree%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20is%2C%20you%20can%20easily%20get%20to%20a%20point%20where%20you%20start%20thinking%20about%20self-improving%2C%20self-replicating%20software%20as%20something%20that%20you%20completely%20lose%20control%20over.%20And%20that%2C%20at%20least%2C%20is%20an%20area%20where%20you%20can%20start%20getting%20some%20scary%20thoughts.%20My%20own%20feeling%20is%20that%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%20there%20are%20ways%20we%20can%20approach%20this%2C%20where%20control%20is%20built%20in.%20Look%20at%20automobiles.%20You%20could%20say%20that%20automobiles%20could%20be%20God-like.%20They%20could%20be%20all%20over%20the%20place%2C%20running%20people%20over%20and%20creating%20accidents.%20And%20yet%2C%20we%20have%20come%20up%20with%20lots%20of%20rules%20and%20regulations%20and%20safety%20standards.%20There%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20automotive%20deaths%2C%20but%20we've%20been%20able%20to%20use%20this%20technology%20very%20effectively.%20So%2C%20my%20hope%20is%20that%20we'll%20do%20the%20same%20with%20AI%2C%20instead%20of%20just%20thinking%20of%20it%20as%20an%20existential%20risk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIsn't%20one%20of%20the%20key%20factors%20here%20the%20degree%20of%20competition%3F%20As%20long%20as%20we%20have%20a%20variety%20of%20players%2C%20the%20likelihood%20of%20it%20going%20out%20of%20control%20is%20way%20smaller%20than%20if%20we%20only%20have%20one%20or%20two%20entities.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20argue%20it%20both%20ways%2C%20can't%20you%3F%20If%20there%20are%20a%20few%20players%2C%20you%20can%20control%20them.%20But%20with%20many%20players%2C%20it's%20harder%20to%20control.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20the%20only%20mechanism%20we%20have%20is%20governments.%20We%20can%20talk%20about%20lots%20of%20things%2C%20but%20in%20our%20system%2C%20it's%20about%20the%20G7%20having%20a%20set%20of%20standards.%20That's%20why%20I%20think%20the%20US%20and%20Europe%20have%20a%20massive%20role%20to%20play.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20heard%20the%20American%20regulator%2C%20Lina%20Khan%20of%20the%20FTC%2C%20say%20we%20need%20a%20transatlantic%20solution.%20Would%20you%20agree%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20100%25.%20I%20believe%20that%20the%20more%20we%20can%20get%20to%20a%20place%20in%20AI%20where%20there%20are%20global%20standards%2C%20the%20better.%20And%20for%20global%20standards%20to%20work%2C%20the%20US%20and%20Europe%20have%20to%20come%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20would%20like%20to%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3Etouch%20on%20a%20topic%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20a%20publisher%2C%20or%20rather%20of%20all%20creative%20industries.%20It's%20very%20important%20for%20those%20who%20create%20intellectual%20property%2C%20that%20they%20continue%20to%20have%20an%20incentive%20to%20work.%20So%2C%20there%20has%20to%20be%20a%20business%20model%20behind%20it.%20Do%20you%20have%20any%20idea%20whether%20and%20how%20the%20big%20AI%20players%20could%20help%20these%20businesses%20to%20keep%20a%20business%20model%20and%20be%20rewarded%20when%20their%20IP%20is%20used%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20right.%20At%20the%20core%20of%20it%2C%20the%20value%20exchange%20here%20has%20to%20be%20more%20beneficial%20to%20the%20publishers.%20We%20know%20that%2C%20with%20the%20current%20state%20of%20the%20internet%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20aggregation%20points%20where%20most%20of%20the%20economic%20rent%20is%20collected.%20And%20only%20very%20few%20breadcrumbs%20are%20thrown%20to%20the%20others%20in%20economic%20terms.%20I%20feel%20that%2C%20if%20there's%20more%20competition%20at%20any%20aggregation%20point%2C%20whether%20it's%20just%20social%20media%2C%20or%20other%20sources%20of%20traffic%2C%20the%20people%20who%20benefit%20directly%20will%20be%20the%20publishers.%20The%20more%20LLMs%20there%20are%20out%20there%20being%20used%20by%20people%20as%20aggregation%20points%2C%20the%20more%20these%20LLMs%20can%20drive%20traffic%20back.%20And%20that%20is%20actually%20a%20good%20thing%20for%20publishers.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20do%20you%20have%20any%20idea%20how%20it%20could%20be%20done%20in%20concrete%20terms%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20that%20there%20are%20two%20things%20here%3A%20one%20is%20that%2C%20in%20a%20large%20language%20model%20like%20BingChat%2C%20for%20example%2C%20we%20have%20at%20least%20tried%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20everything%20that%20is%20a%20response%20is%20actually%20linked.%20Our%20goal%20is%20to%20first%20contract%20with%20our%20publishers%20and%20find%20out%20if%20we%20can%20drive%20traffic%20back%20through%20citations%20and%20links.%20Second%20is%20to%20think%20about%20the%20revenue%20share%20of%20any%20advertising%20revenue%20with%20the%20publishers.%20I%20feel%20that%20that's%20our%20starting%20point%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20what%20we%20are%20doing%20together%20rests%20on%20that.%20There%20are%20some%20complications%20going%20forward.%20After%20all%2C%20with%20synthetic%20data%20training%2C%20I%20think%20that%20the%20incentive%20is%20that%20we%20create%20more%20synthetic%20data.%20And%20if%20you're%20training%20on%20synthetic%20data%2C%20where%20you%20don't%20have%20stable%20attribution%20to%20likeness%2C%20that%20becomes%20a%20hard%20thing.%20So%2C%20there%20is%20some%20technological%20disruption%20we%20will%20have%20to%20be%20mindful%20of.%20The%20fact%20is%2C%20that%20no%20publisher%20will%20allow%20you%20to%20crawl%20their%20content%20if%20there%20isn't%20a%20value%20exchange%2C%20and%20the%20value%20exchange%20has%20to%20come%20in%20two%20forms.%20One%20is%20traffic%2C%20and%20the%20other%20is%20revenue%20share.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20coups%20you%20landed%20was%20definitely%20the%20investment%20in%20Open%20AI.%20Could%20you%20give%20us%20a%20little%20background%20on%20how%20this%20came%20about%20and%20how%20your%20conversations%20with%20Sam%20Altman%20went%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20known%20Sam%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20I%20knew%20him%20when%20he%20had%20his%20first%20startup%2C%20and%20I%20kept%20in%20touch%20with%20him%20over%20the%20years.%20We%20started%20working%20with%20Sam%20in%202016%20as%20one%20of%20the%20first%20cloud%20providers%20that%20gave%20them%20a%20lot%20of%20credits.%20In%202018%20or%202019%2C%20Sam%20came%20to%20us%20and%20said%20they%20needed%20more%20investment%20in%20terms%20of%20compute.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222222%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Altman%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20OpenAI%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65233bd168f1d46f52ab69ac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESam%20Altman%2C%20CEO%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20which%20has%20partnered%20with%20Microsoft%20on%20AI%20efforts.%3Cp%3ETomohiro%20Ohsumi%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20wasn't%20it%20a%20non-profit%20project%20at%20that%20time%20as%20well%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorrect.%20I%20think%2C%20fundamentally%2C%20they're%20still%20a%20non-profit%2C%20but%20they%20needed%20to%20create%20a%20for-profit%20entity%20that%20could%20then%20essentially%20fund%20the%20compute.%20And%20we%20were%20really%20willing%20to%20take%20the%20bet%20early%20on%20what%20was%20then%20essentially%20a%20non-profit%20entity.%20The%20fact%20that%20we%20were%20able%20to%20build%20and%20get%20Copilot%20and%20ChatGPT%20up%20and%20running%20made%20me%20very%20confident%20that%20there's%20something%20different%20about%20this%20generation%20of%20AI%20and%20what%20it's%20doing.%20Its%20application%20in%20GitHub%20made%20me%20even%20more%20confident%20that%20you%20can%20build%20something%20really%20useful%2C%20and%20not%20just%20have%20a%20technological%20breakthrough.%20So%2C%20we%20went%20all%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMany%20years%20ago%2C%20you%20told%20me%20about%20your%20motivation%20to%20create%20competition%20with%20Google%20in%20search.%20You%20once%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20make%20Google%20dance.%26quot%3B%20Is%20Google%20dancing%20yet%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo.%20I%20think%2C%20when%20you%20have%20three%20percent%20share%20of%20global%20search%2C%20and%20you're%20competing%20with%20somebody%20who%20has%2097%20percent%2C%20even%20a%20small%20gain%20here%20and%20there%20is%20an%20exciting%20moment.%20But%20Google%20is%20a%20very%20strong%20company%2C%20and%20they%20are%20going%20to%20come%20out%20strong.%20Bard%20is%20a%20very%20competitive%20product%20already.%20And%20they%20have%20a%20new%20model%20with%20Gemini.%20Google%20has%20a%20number%20of%20structural%20advantages%20right%20there%3A%20they%20already%20have%20the%20share%2C%20they%20control%20Android%2C%20they%20control%20Chrome.%20I%20always%20say%20that%20Google%20makes%20more%20money%20on%20Windows%20than%20all%20of%20Microsoft.%20It%20keeps%20us%20grounded.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20Google%20has%20to%20disrupt%20itself.%20Basically%2C%20generative%20AI%20chatbots%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20replace%20search%20as%20we%20know%20it.%20At%20least%2C%20I%20use%20it%20like%20that.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20whenever%20I%20had%20a%20question%2C%20I%20used%20to%20put%20it%20in%20Google.%20Now%20I%20put%20it%20into%20Bing%20Chat%20or%20Bard.%20It%20creates%20a%20different%20user%20behavior%2C%20which%20could%20eventually%20lead%20to%20a%20fundamental%20change%20in%20user%20habits.%20Don't%20you%20agree%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20right.%20I%20think%20you're%20fundamentally%20speaking%20about%20changes%20in%20user%20habits.%20But%20that's%20proving%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20harder%20than%20you%20might%20think%2C%20because%20the%20strength%20of%20Google%20is%20the%20default%20nature%20of%20the%20Google%20search.%20It's%20so%20ingrained%20as%20a%20search%20habit%2C%20and%20change%20is%20moving%20slowly.%20But%20having%20said%20that%2C%20you%20made%20a%20good%20point%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20us%20today%20are%20now%20going%20to%20Bing%20Chat%20or%20to%20ChatGPT%20or%20Bard%20to%20have%20our%20questions%20answered.%20I%20think%20things%20are%20changing%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20slow-moving%20transition.%20Google%20can%20make%20that%20transition%2C%20and%20they're%20very%20much%20committed%20to%20making%20it.%20And%20you're%20right%20in%20pointing%20out%20that%20their%20business%20model%20will%20fundamentally%20have%20to%20change.%20So%2C%20it's%20a%20little%20bit%20like%20what%20happened%20to%20us%20with%20Windows.%20We%20had%20a%20fantastic%20business%20model%20until%20it%20wasn't%20anymore.%20Therefore%2C%20I%20think%20Google%20will%20be%20facing%20more%20challenges%2C%20and%20will%20have%20to%20fundamentally%20rethink%20its%20business%20model%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20But%20they%20definitely%20have%20a%20head%20start%2C%20because%20they%20already%20have%20all%20the%20users.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20things%20are%20developing%20so%20fast.%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20you%20sometimes%20use%20Any%20Call.%20It's%20such%20a%20nice%20feature%20where%20you%20can%20just%20give%20a%20voice%20command%20or%20ask%20a%20question%2C%20and%20you%20immediately%20get%20answers%20even%20to%20very%20sophisticated%20questions.%20Nobody%20knows%20how%20user%20habits%20will%20change.%20Do%20you%20have%20a%20vision%3F%20What%20is%20your%20most%20radical%2C%20your%20most%20disruptive%20vision%20for%20the%20future%20of%20our%20habits%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Copilot%20for%20example%3A%20The%20way%20we%20are%20building%20it%20is%20to%20say%2C%20I%20want%20to%20use%20it%20to%20plan%20my%20vacation%20or%20do%20some%20shopping%20or%20write%20some%20code%20or%20prepare%20for%20a%20meeting.%20It's%20kind%20of%20like%20a%20personal%20agent%20to%20me.%20It's%20kind%20of%20like%20the%20original%20PC.%20What%20was%20the%20PC%20about%3F%20It%20was%20about%20empowering%20you%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20things.%20Now%2C%20Copilot%20is%20in%20many%20ways%20like%20a%20PC%2C%20except%20that%20one%20can%20just%20go%20to%20this%20personal%20agent%20and%20say%2C%20Write%20me%20a%20document.%20I'm%20meeting%20Mathias%2C%20please%20prepare%20me%20for%20that%20meeting%20with%20all%20the%20summarization%20of%20all%20my%20mails%20from%20our%20partnership%2C%20and%20it%20comes%20back%20with%20all%20that.%20It's%20kind%20of%20like%20asking%20an%20assistant%2C%20a%20smart%20analyst%2C%20about%20all%20the%20things%20you%20want.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20I%20find%20so%20fascinating%2C%20is%20that%20we%20humans%20are%20now%20trying%20to%20deal%20with%20this%20disruptive%20change%2C%20which%20may%20be%20more%20important%20than%20the%20invention%20of%20the%20internet%20or%20the%20invention%20of%20the%20automobile%2C%20by%20defining%20the%20limits%20of%20what%20AI%20can%20or%20cannot%20do.%20And%20I%20am%20constantly%20discovering%20that%20I%20was%20wrong.%20A%20couple%20of%20months%20ago%2C%20I%20thought%20AI%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20have%20or%20create%20emotions.%20But%20AI%20does%20it%20perfectly%20well%2C%20perhaps%20even%20better%20than%20human%20beings%2C%20who%20are%20not%20as%20good%20at%20faking%20emotions%20sometimes.%20Or%20take%20creativity%20or%20humor%2C%20we%20always%20say%20AI%20cannot%20do%20that.%20It's%20not%20true.%20Do%20you%20see%20any%20limits%20today%3F%20Or%20do%20you%20think%20we%20should%20define%20some%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20I%20see%20it%2C%20as%20someone%20in%20the%20business%20of%20creating%20more%20powerful%20and%20capable%20AI%2C%20is%20that%20I%20wouldn't%20bet%20against%20it.%20My%20question%20is%20rather%2C%20what%20will%20humans%20do%20with%20more%20capable%20AI%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20mean%2C%20would%20Picasso%20be%20better%20with%20AI%20or%20without%20it%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20exactly.%20If%20we%20have%20a%20new%20tool%2C%20what%20will%20we%20do%20with%20it%3F%20What%20did%20we%20do%20with%20cars%3F%20What%20did%20we%20do%20with%20planes%3F%20What%20can%20we%20do%20with%20computers%20today%3F%20We've%20done%20a%20lot%20of%20interesting%20things.%20I%20am%20betting%20on%20human%20ingenuity%20to%20do%20things%20with%20this%20new%20tool.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20exciting%20things%20for%20me%20is%20that%2C%20if%20you%20think%20about%20it%2C%20eight%20billion%20people%20can%20have%20a%20doctor%2C%20a%20management%20consultant%2C%20a%20tutor%2C%20and%20more%20in%20their%20pocket.%20It's%20a%20true%20democratization%20of%20knowledge.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221624%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ChatGPT%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f8b9b7f1210f00198493a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221218%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI's%20popular%20generative%20AI%20chatbot%2C%20ChatGPT%2C%20which%20is%20available%20on%20both%20the%20web%20and%20as%20a%20mobile%20app.%3Cp%3EJakub%20Porzycki%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EBritish%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20AI%20expert%20Mustafa%20Suleyman%20is%20convinced%20that%20AI%20is%20particularly%20strong%20in%20this%20emotional%20context%20of%20things.%20Would%20you%20agree%20with%20him%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20he's%20right%20in%20some%20sense.%20We've%20been%20working%20with%20Epic%20software%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20healthcare%20ISVs%20in%20the%20United%20States%20that%20everybody%20uses.%20A%20significant%20portion%20of%20the%20US%20healthcare%20system%20uses%20their%20medical%20record%20system.%20And%20they%20were%20telling%20me%20about%20how%20some%20of%20the%20doctors%20are%20finding%20that%20the%20drafts%20that%20AI%20is%20creating%20for%20them%20are%20very%20empathetic.%20Human%20beings%20are%20sometimes%20inconsistent%20in%20how%20we%20express%20ourselves%2C%20whereas%20the%20AI%20can%20be%20more%20consistent.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20writing%20a%20job%20description%2C%20it%20can%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20job%20description%20invites%20people%20of%20all%20genders%20and%20persuasions%20to%20apply%20and%20not%20have%20bias.%20So%2C%20I%20think%20AI%20can%20actually%20be%20very%20helpful%20in%20many%20ways%20to%20be%20a%20little%20more%20empathetic%20and%20more%20understanding%20of%20the%20world.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20recently%20interviewed%20a%20virtual%20version%20of%20Axel%20Springer%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20namesake%20of%20our%20company.%20I%20asked%20him%20really%20tough%20questions%20about%20culture%20and%20soft-factor%20issues%2C%20and%20found%20his%20answers%20more%20convincing%20than%20my%20own%2C%20I%20have%20to%20say.%20Do%20you%20see%20any%20reason%20or%20danger%20that%20humans%20will%20end%20up%20serving%20machines%20instead%20of%20machines%20serving%20humans%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20the%20question.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThat%20is%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Ethe%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Equestion.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20is%2C%20how%20do%20you%20stay%20in%20control%3F%20And%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20how%20can%20we%20ensure%20that%20AI%20does%20not%20manipulate%20human%20beings%2C%20even%20in%20this%20cognizant%20context%20of%20empathy.%20It%20cannot%20use%20its%20soft%20skills%20to%20manipulate%20humans.%20So%20I%20think%20there%20will%20be%20this%20level%20of%20thinking%20about%20software%20and%20its%20verification.%20About%20how%20it%20will%20be%20deployed%2C%20how%20will%20it%20be%20monitored%2C%20what%20adverse%20activities%20will%20be%20happening.%20These%20are%20some%20of%20the%20frontiers%2C%20what%20is%20considered%20the%20alignment%20challenge.%20Another%20challenge%20is%20understanding%20how%20AI%20makes%20its%20own%20decisions%20inside%20the%20box.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20it%20thinking%20consciously%3F%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20question.%20We%20don't%20even%20fully%20understand%20what%20consciousness%20is.%20You%20can%20see%20it%20from%20a%20neuroscience%20perspective%2C%20but%20can%20we%20mathematically%20or%20mechanistically%20understand%20how%20LLMs%20do%20their%20predictions%2C%20for%20example%3F%20It's%20a%20frontier%20of%20science%20where%20there%20is%20still%20work%20being%20done.%C2%A0%20You%20have%20to%20be%20very%2C%20very%20conscious%20of%20how%20you%20deploy%20what%20we%20have%20today%20in%20ways%20that%20human%20agency%2C%20and%20humanity%2C%20is%20in%20the%20loop.%20Human%20agency%20and%20judgment%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20very%20much%20part%20of%20the%20loop.%20And%20we%20must%20not%20lose%20control.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIf%20AI%20has%20such%20strong%20intellectual%20ability%20(IQ)%20and%20emotional%20intelligence%20(EQ)%2C%20and%20is%20even%20good%20at%20creativity%2C%20humor%2C%20self-improvement%2C%20and%20accelerating%20progress%3B%20what%20areas%20of%20intelligence%20are%20left%20for%20humans%3F%20And%20what%20advice%20would%20you%20give%20mankind%20concerning%20what%20to%20focus%20on%20in%20the%20next%20decades%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20look%20at%20this%20new%20example%20of%20the%20inverted%20classroom%2C%20where%20people%20are%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BLook%2C%20we%20know%20you're%20going%20to%20use%20one%20of%20the%20LLMs%2C%20like%20Bing%20Chat%20or%20ChatGPT%2C%20for%20your%20assignments.%20What%20we%20want%20to%20know%20are%20the%20prompts.%20We'll%20give%20you%20the%20answer%2C%20now%20tell%20us%20the%20prompts.%26quot%3B%20That's%20critical%20thinking.%20Because%20you%20learn%20so%20much%20more.%20I%20think%20that%20critical%20thinking%2C%20good%20judgment%2C%20how%20to%20think%20in%20a%20broad%20way%2C%20and%20not%20being%20afraid%20to%20learn%2C%20could%20be%20the%20new%20benefits.%20I%20sometimes%20say%20to%20myself%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20God%2C%20I%20wish%20I%20understood%20more%20biology.%26quot%3B%20And%20now%20I%20can%20ask%20dumb%20questions%20and%20have%20things%20explained%20at%20my%20pace.%20Our%20ability%20to%20consume%20more%20knowledge%20and%20to%20grow%20our%20own%20knowledge%20base%20can%20improve.%20I%20think%20there'll%20be