ms%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20proximity%20and%20exposure%2C%20believe%20these%20falsehoods%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20causes%20this%20directional%20bias%2C%20motivated%20reasoning%20and%20psychological%20impulses%20to%20propagate%20falsehoods%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20scholarly%20research%20of%20Dagher%2C%20Silverman%20and%20Kaltenthaler%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fisq%2Farticle%2F65%2F3%2F798%2F6121613%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3ESeeing%20Is%20Disbelieving%3A%20The%20Depths%20and%20Limits%20of%20Factual%20Misinformation%20in%20War%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eexplains%20how%20from%20World%20War%20II%20to%20the%20invasion%20of%20Iraq%2C%20war%20has%20always%20been%20rife%20with%20lies.%20They%20have%20questioned%20how%20the%20proliferation%20of%20fake%20news%2C%20misinformation%20and%20pervasive%20rumours%20eventually%20initiates%2C%20catalyses%20and%20provokes%20further%20violent%20aggression.%20This%20dystopian%20nihilism%20can%20be%20contextualised%20in%20the%20ongoing%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%2C%20where%20the%20concoction%20of%20geo-politics%20of%20emotions%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ereal%20politik%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20has%20furthered%20the%20diabolic%20interests%20of%20%E2%80%98atrocity%20propaganda.%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMarc%20Owen%20Jones%2C%20Associate%20Professor%20of%20Middle%20East%20Studies%20at%20Hamad%20bin%20Khalifa%20University%20at%20Doha%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fmarcowenjones%2Fstatus%2F1714196259584540804%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20five%20strategies%20of%20disinformation%20warfare.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20First%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20say%20something%20else.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecondly%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20ensure%20enough%20people%20use%20false%20information%20so%20that%20it%20becomes%20a%20%E2%80%98narrative.%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EThirdly%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20when%20it%20becomes%20a%20narrative%2C%20it%20then%20has%20to%20be%20%E2%80%98debunked%E2%80%99%2C%20unfairly%20putting%20burden%20of%20proof%20on%20journalists%2C%20etc.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EFourthly%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20debunking%20comes%20too%20late.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ELastly%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20the%20damage%20is%20done.%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20narrative%20put%20forward%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.stjohns.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D1104%26context%3Djovsa%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMinna%20Aslama%20Horowitz%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20an%20expert%20on%20digital%20rights%20and%20advocacy%2C%20Central%20European%20University%2C%20has%20explained%20how%20%E2%80%9Cdisinformation%20often%20through%20cyberwars%20and%20information%20disorder%20is%20manifested%20in%20many%20frontiers%20and%20for%20numerous%20reasons%2C%20including%20monetary%20gain%20and%20political%20power.%20An%20individual%E2%80%99s%20frustrations%20about%20social%20and%20economic%20conditions%20can%20turn%20into%20the%20fear%2C%20hatred%2C%20and%20vitriol%20that%20prompt%20simple%20acts%20of%20digital%20violence%2C%20such%20as%20creating%2C%20commenting%20on%2C%20and%20sharing%20rumors%2C%20falsehoods%2C%20and%20hate%20speech.%20Hence%2C%20information%20wars%20have%20many%20more%20soldiers%20than%20do%20cyberwars.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EScholars%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fprofile%2FCorneliu-Bjola%2Fpublication%2F346440120_Public_Diplomacy_in_the_Age_of_%2527Post-reality%2527%2Flinks%2F63f7f6f257495059453933ac%2FPublic-Diplomacy-in-the-Age-of-Post-reality.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIlan%20Manor%20and%20Corneliu%20Bjola%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20have%20explained%20that%20currently%20we%20are%20witnessing%20the%20age%20of%20%E2%80%98post%20reality%E2%80%99%20which%20is%20characterised%20by%20states%20fracturing%2C%20contesting%20and%20assaulting%20reality.%20The%20driving%20force%20behind%20%E2%80%98post-reality%E2%80%99%20is%20digitalisation%20through%20which%20states%20create%20a%20world%20of%20competing%20realities%20which%20erode%20social%20cohesion%2C%20amplify%20social%20tensions%2C%20drive%20social%20frustration%20and%20prevent%20individuals%20from%20making%20sense%20of%20the%20world%20around%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20now%20that%20we%20are%20tightly%20incarcerated%20in%20the%20world%20of%20falsehoods%2C%20propaganda%2C%20deep-fakes%2C%20sock-puppets%20and%20voice%20clones%2C%20how%20do%20we%20understand%20what%20is%20true%3F%20The%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%20has%20become%20a%20mouthpiece%20for%20Islamophobia%20and%20further%20causing%20divisions%20between%20Judaism%20and%20Islam.%20Martyrdom%20and%20political%20violence%2C%20cloaked%20by%20religious%20propaganda%20has%20added%20fuel%20to%20this%20%E2%80%98post-reality%E2%80%99%20we%20live%20in%20%E2%80%93%20an%20apocalyptic%20nightmare%20where%20human%20lives%20are%20rendered%20meaningless%20in%20invisible%20ignominy%20and%20hatred.%20The%20debates%20on%20asymmetrical%20balance%20of%20power%20and%20the%20apartheid%20occupation%20of%20Israel%20through%20illegal%20settlements%20are%20being%20replaced%20by%20the%20politics%20of%20deception%2C%20denial%20and%20distortion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20I%20write%20this%2C%20the%20world%20has%20forgotten%20that%20on%20December%207%2C%202022%2C%20an%20Israeli%20Zionist%20soldier%20Yosed%20Diamont%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fincontextmedia%2Fstatus%2F1600493875746963457%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20an%20interview%20to%20Israeli%20Channel%20Hot%208%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20openly%20confessed%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20put%20Palestinians%20in%20cages%20and%20killed%20them.%20One%20of%20us%20raped%20a%2016-year-old%20girl%3B%20some%20of%20us%20ran%20after%20them%20with%20flame%20throwers%20and%20burned%20them.%E2%80%9D%20Or%20that%20as%20of%20today%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freliefweb.int%2Freport%2Foccupied-palestinian-territory%2Fisrael-destroys-quarter-northern-gaza-strip-palestinian-death-toll-exceeds-4000-enar%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520documentation%2520by%2520Euro%2Cthem%2520being%2520children%2520and%2520women.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edeath%20toll%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20risen%20to%204%2C079%20with%20more%20than%2015%2C000%20wounded.%20And%20this%20is%20just%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20end.%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EDr.%20Shubhda%20Chaudhary%20is%20a%20West%20Asia%20political%20analyst%20and%20editor%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20India%20West%20Asia%20Dialogue.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697942139000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19124105%2Fgazarimal_2023-10-18_195802.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fdenial-deception-and-distortion-the-atrocity-propaganda-war-in-israel-and-palestine%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Who%20believes%20in%20falsehoods%20and%20lies%20in%20war-torn%20regions%3F%20Do%20the%20victims%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20proximity%20and%20exposure%2C%20believe%20these%20falsehoods%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fdenial-deception-and-distortion-the-atrocity-propaganda-war-in-israel-and-palestine%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Standards%20Were%20Created%20to%20Fit%20the%20SC's%20Denial%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Marry%20to%20LGBTQ%20People%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20in%20a%20series%20of%20pieces%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20marriage%20equality%20judgment.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20week%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20delivered%20its%20judgement%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2022%2F36593%2F36593_2022_1_1501_47792_Judgement_17-Oct-2023.pdf%5C%22%3ESupriyo%20%40%20Supriya%20Chakraborty%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20accepting%20the%20existence%20of%20the%20manifold%20disadvantages%20faced%20by%20non-heterosexual%20couples%2C%20while%20simultaneously%20refusing%20to%20express%20such%20disadvantages%20in%20the%20language%20of%20constitutional%20transgressions%2C%20or%20to%20grant%20the%20petitioners%20any%20relief%20other%20than%20affirming%20the%20Union%E2%80%99s%20vague%20promise%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9CHigh-Powered%20Committee%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20series%2C%20I%20propose%20that%20the%20instant%20case%20constitutes%20an%20immense%20setback%20in%20at%20least%20three%20aspects%20of%20fundamental%20rights%20jurisprudence%20%E2%80%93%20unenumerated%20rights%2C%20positive%20rights%2C%20and%20permissible%20classifications%20%E2%80%93%20whose%20many%20well-settled%20propositions%20have%20been%20substantially%20eroded%20in%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20pursuit%20of%20institutional%20abstention.%20Before%20I%20begin%2C%20it%20must%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20court%20has%20laid%20down%20the%20following%20propositions%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Col%3E%20%3Cli%3EUnanimously%2C%20that%20marriage%20cannot%20be%20elevated%20to%20a%20fundamental%20right%2C%20and%20the%20deprivation%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20marry%E2%80%9D%20cannot%20be%20assailed%20under%20Articles%2019(1)(a)%20or%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EUnanimously%2C%20that%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F594580%2F%5C%22%3ESection%204%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201954%20(%E2%80%9CSMA%E2%80%9D)%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1088723%2F%5C%22%3ESection%204%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Foreign%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201969%20(%E2%80%9CFMA%E2%80%9D)%2C%20which%20conceptualise%20marriage%20thereunder%20heteronormatively%2C%20are%20valid%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EWith%20a%203%3A2%20split%20(Justices%20Bhat%2C%20Narasimha%20and%20Kohli%20speaking%20for%20the%20majority)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1573489%2F%5C%22%3ESection%2057(2)%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20Juvenile%20Justice%20Act%2C%202015%20(%E2%80%9CJJ%20Act%E2%80%9D)%2C%20which%20confines%20adoption%20rights%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccouple%5Bs%5D%E2%80%9D%2C%20refers%20only%20to%20married%20couples.%20Regulation%205(3)%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcara.wcd.gov.in%2FPDF%2Fadoption%2520regulations%25202022%2520english_27.pdf%5C%22%3EAdoption%20Regulations%2C%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20prescribes%20%E2%80%9Ctwo%20years%20of%20stable%20marital%20relationship%E2%80%9D%20as%20an%20eligibility%20criterion%20for%20adopting%2C%20is%20intra%20vires%20the%20JJ%20Act%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EUnanimously%2C%20that%20the%20effective%20prohibition%20on%20queer%20couples%20jointly%20adopting%20a%20child%20is%20indirectly%20discriminatory.%20With%20a%203%3A2%20split%20(Justices%20Bhat%2C%20Narasimha%20and%20Kohli%2C%20speaking%20for%20the%20majority)%2C%20such%20indirect%20discrimination%20%E2%80%93%20along%20with%20other%20disadvantages%20faced%20by%20queer%20couples%20%E2%80%93%20must%20be%20%E2%80%9Csuitably%20redressed%20and%20removed%20by%20the%20State%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20cannot%20be%20remedied%20through%20the%20judicial%20route%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EWith%20a%203%3A2%20split%20(Justices%20Bhat%2C%20Narasimha%20and%20Kohli%2C%20speaking%20for%20the%20majority)%2C%20a%20combined%20reading%20of%20Articles%2019(1)(c)%2C%2019(1)(e)%2C%2021%20and%2025%20does%20not%20warrant%20the%20imposition%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpositive%20obligation%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20state%20to%20recognise%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccivil%20union%E2%80%9D%20of%20same-sex%20couples%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EUnanimously%2C%20that%20transgender%20persons%20in%20heterosexual%20relationships%20can%20marry%20both%20under%20personal%20law%20and%20the%20SMA.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Fol%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20series%20of%20pieces%2C%20I%20examine%20the%20judgement%20on%20the%20first%20four%20counts%2C%20arguing%20that%20it%20constitutes%2C%20overall%2C%20an%20attempt%20by%20the%20court%20to%20justify%20its%20institutional%20abstention%20through%20delegitimising%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20case.%20This%20is%20done%20through%20denying%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20right%20to%20marry%2C%20misidentifying%20the%20classification%E2%80%99s%20subject-matter%2C%20and%20creating%20artificial%20barriers%20on%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20transform%20social%20structures.%20In%20this%20piece%2C%20I%20examine%20the%20first%20mode%20of%20delegitimisation%20%E2%80%93%20the%20denial%20of%20a%20right%20to%20marry%20%E2%80%93%20arguing%20that%20such%20denial%20was%20achieved%20through%20the%20creation%20of%20three%20never-before-seen%20standards%2C%20which%20were%20specifically%20tailored%20to%20reach%20the%20conclusion%20of%20the%20non-existence%20of%20a%20right%20to%20marry.%20I%20also%20propose%20that%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20right%20to%20marry%20was%20designed%20as%20a%20red%20herring%2C%20and%20adherence%20to%20existing%20constitutional%20doctrine%20that%20prefers%20an%20examination%20of%20a%20restriction%E2%80%99s%20reasonableness%20instead%20of%20a%20right%E2%80%99s%20existence%20would%20have%20yielded%20a%20better%2C%20constitutionally-compliant%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20make%20this%20argument%20in%20the%20following%20manner%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0first%2C%20I%20examine%20the%20three%20opinions%20on%20the%20right%20to%20marry%2C%20laying%20down%20and%20clarifying%20the%20standards%20employed%20therein%3B%C2%A0second%2C%20I%20propose%20that%20the%20three%20standards%20are%20largely%20unfounded%2C%20in%20that%20they%20have%20no%20basis%20in%20case-law%2C%20and%20make%20little%20logical%20sense%20when%20applied%20to%20unenumerated%20rights%20already%20elevated%20as%20fundamental%3B%20and%C2%A0third%2C%20I%20propose%20that%20the%20question%20of%20the%20right%20to%20marry%20was%20unimportant%2C%20and%20the%20case%20could%20have%20been%20decided%20in%20reference%20to%20existing%20doctrine%2C%20where%20the%20Court%20assesses%20a%20restriction%E2%80%99s%20validity%20instead%20of%20a%20right%E2%80%99s%20existence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Restrictive%20Conceptualisation%20of%20Unenumerated%20Rights%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Court%20on%20the%20Right%20to%20Marry%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioners%2C%20based%20on%20precedent%20locating%20marriage%20in%20the%20values%20of%20expression%2C%20dignity%20and%20autonomy%2C%20urged%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20right%20to%20marry%20under%20Articles%2019(1)(a)%20and%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20which%20the%20state%20was%20unjustifiably%20restricting%20for%20same-sex%20couples%20u%2Fs%204%20of%20the%20SMA.%20Such%20unjustifiability%20arose%20due%20to%20its%20incompatibility%20with%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdecency%20or%20morality%E2%80%9D%20clause%20under%20Article%2019(2)%2C%20which%20had%20been%20previously%20interpreted%20by%20the%20Court%20to%20mean%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20morality%E2%80%9D%20instead%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20morality%E2%80%9D.%20Additionally%2C%20it%20was%20argued%20that%20the%20restriction%20impinged%20on%20same-sex%20couples%E2%80%99%20dignity%20without%20fulfilling%20the%20proportionality%20standard%2C%20for%20the%20Union%20failed%20to%20demonstrate%20even%20a%20%E2%80%9Clegitimate%20state%20aim%E2%80%9D%20for%20restricting%20marriage%20to%20heterosexual%20couples%20distinct%20from%20%E2%80%9Cbare%20animus%20against%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20rejected%20this%20argument%20at%20its%20very%20first%20prong%2C%20holding%20that%20there%20exists%20no%20right%20to%20marry%20under%20the%20constitution%2C%20rendering%20an%20assessment%20of%20the%20validity%20of%20its%20denial%20to%20same-sex%20couples%20unnecessary.%20The%20three%20judgements%20(Justice%20Kaul%2C%20concurring%20with%20CJI%20Chandrachud)%20offer%20their%20own%2C%20separate%20reasons%20in%20refusing%20to%20elevate%20marriage%20to%20the%20level%20of%20a%20fundamental%20right.%20Justice%20Bhat%20finds%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20non-involvement%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20marital%20institution%20fatal%20(%C2%B645-6)%3B%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20finds%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20excessive%20involvement%20in%20creating%20the%20contemporary%20significance%20of%20marriage%20fatal%20(%C2%B6183)%3B%20and%20Justice%20Narasimha%20finds%20the%20persistence%20of%20%E2%80%9Ccustomary%20practices%20and%20religious%20beliefs%E2%80%9D%20governing%20marriage%20as%20demonstrating%20its%20status%20as%20ab-initio%20restricted%2C%20rendering%20moot%20the%20question%20of%20its%20status%20as%20a%20right%20(%C2%B612).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Bhat%2C%20writing%20for%20the%20majority%2C%20offers%20two%20reasons%20to%20deny%20marriage%20the%20status%20of%20a%20fundamental%20right%20%E2%80%93first%2C%20that%20marriage%20is%20prior%20to%2C%20and%20external%20to%20the%20state%2C%20for%20the%20state%20only%20%E2%80%9Cutilize%5Bs%5D%20or%20accommodate%5Bs%5D%E2%80%9D%20a%20wholly%20independent%20structure%3B%20and%C2%A0second%2C%20since%20marriage%20is%20a%20non-state%20institution%2C%20any%20recognition%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfundamental%20right%20to%20marry%E2%80%9D%20requires%20a%20horizontal%20conceptualisation%2C%20a%20task%20the%20Court%20cannot%20undertake%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E45.%C2%A0%E2%80%A6%5BM%5Darriage%20existed%20and%20exists%2C%20historically%20and%20chronologically%20in%20all%20of%20the%20senses%20%E2%80%93%20because%20people%20married%20before%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20state%20as%20a%20concept.%20Therefore%2C%20marriage%20as%20an%20institution%20is%20prior%20to%20the%20state%2C%20i.e.%2C%20it%20precedes%20it%E2%80%A6This%20implies%20that%20the%20marriage%20structure%20exists%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20state%2C%20which%20the%20latter%20can%20utilise%20or%20accommodate%2C%20but%20cannot%20be%20abolished%20as%20a%20concept.%20Under%20this%20view%20terms%20of%20marriage%20are%20set%2C%20to%20a%20large%20extent%2C%20independently%20of%20the%20state.%20Its%20source%20is%20external%20to%20the%20state.%20That%20source%20defines%20the%20boundaries%20of%20marriage.%20This%20implies%20that%20state%20power%20to%20regulate%20marriage%20does%20not%20sit%20easy%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20marriage%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E46.%C2%A0If%20indeed%20there%20is%20a%20right%20to%20marry%20unless%20it%20is%20elevated%20to%20a%20right%20akin%20to%20Articles%2017%2C%2023%2C%20and%2024%2C%20%5Bwhich%20apply%20to%20both%20state%20and%20nonstate%20agencies%20and%20actors%5D%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20operationalized%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20Justice%20Bhat%2C%20therefore%2C%20for%20an%20unenumerated%20right%20to%20be%20elevated%20to%20the%20level%20of%20a%20fundamental%20right%2C%20its%20existence%20%E2%80%93%20at%20least%20in%20part%20%E2%80%93%20must%20be%20owed%20to%20the%20state%2C%20and%20its%20effectuation%20must%20not%20require%20the%20creation%20of%20norms%20governing%20non-state%20persons.%20Essentially%2C%20in%20his%20view%2C%20it%20is%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20non-involvement%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20marital%20institution%20that%20prevents%20access%20thereto%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20offers%20substantially%20contrary%20reasoning%20to%20disqualify%20marriage%20from%20the%20status%20of%20a%20fundamental%20right.%20He%20finds%20that%20instead%20of%20the%20state-independent%20existence%20of%20marriage%2C%20it%20has%20been%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20active%20involvement%20in%20creating%20conditions%20of%20the%20contemporary%20significance%20of%20marriage%20that%20caused%20a%20demand%20for%20its%20constitutionalisation%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20The%20%E2%80%9Cnon-constitutional%E2%80%9D%20origin%20of%20the%20reasons%20necessitating%20the%20elevation%20of%20marriage%20to%20a%20fundamental%20right%2C%20in%20his%20opinion%2C%20prevents%20such%20elevation%20(%C2%B6183).%20In%20buttressing%20his%20claim%2C%20he%20lays%20down%20two%20factors%20to%20determine%20when%20an%20unenumerated%20right%20may%20be%20elevated%20as%20fundamental%20%E2%80%93%20first%2C%20a%20specific%20fundamental%20right%20must%20be%20incapable%20of%20being%20properly%20effectuated%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20unenumerated%20right%3B%20or%C2%A0second%2C%20the%20unenumerated%20right%20must%20be%20central%20to%20%E2%80%9Cvalues%20or%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20Constitution%E2%80%9D%20(%C2%B6160-1).%20In%20his%20opinion%2C%20the%20right%20to%20education%20was%20deemed%20a%20fundamental%20right%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1775396%2F%5C%22%3EUnni%20Krishnan%20v.%20State%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0for%20no%20reason%20other%20than%20its%20centrality%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cvalues%20that%20the%20Constitution%20espouses%E2%80%9D%2C%20while%20privacy%20was%20deemed%20a%20fundamental%20right%20in%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F10%2FRight_to_Privacy__Puttaswamy_Judgment_1.pdf%5C%22%3EPuttaswamy%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0independent%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccontent%20given%20to%20privacy%20by%20the%20State%E2%80%9D%20(%C2%B6184).%20He%20notes%20that%20the%20reasons%20necessitating%20marriage%E2%80%99s%20elevation%20to%20a%20fundamental%20right%20have%20been%20coloured%20by%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20conferral%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmaterial%20and%20expressive%E2%80%9D%20benefits%20on%20the%20marital%20union%2C%20an%20insufficient%20justification%20for%20elevation%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E184.%C2%A0The%20arguments%20of%20the%20petitioners%20that%20the%20Constitution%20recognises%20a%20right%20to%20marry%20is%20hinged%20on%20the%20meaning%20accorded%20to%20marriage%20by%20statutes%2C%20which%20cannot%20be%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Narasimha%20finds%20yet%20another%20reason%20why%20marriage%20cannot%20be%20deemed%20fundamental%20%E2%80%93%20even%20though%20the%20state%20has%20legislated%20on%20marriage%2C%20such%20as%20by%20providing%20minimum%20marriageable%20ages%2C%20prohibited%20relations%20and%20modes%20of%20succession%2C%20such%20legislation%20almost%20always%20accommodates%C2%A0customary%20and%20religious%20practices%20governing%20the%20same.%20Such%20accommodation%20of%20religious%20norms%20in%20marriage%2C%20in%20his%20opinion%2C%20means%20that%20marriage%20is%C2%A0ab-initio%C2%A0restricted%2C%20rendering%20moot%20the%20question%20of%20a%C2%A0right%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E12.%C2%A0In%20my%20considered%20opinion%2C%20the%20institutional%20space%20of%20marriage%20is%20conditioned%20and%20occupied%20synchronously%20by%20legislative%20interventions%2C%20customary%20practises%2C%20and%20religious%20beliefs%E2%80%A6Given%20this%20nature%20of%20marriage%20as%20an%20institution%2C%20the%20right%20to%20choose%20a%20spouse%20and%20the%20right%20of%20a%20consenting%20couple%20to%20be%20recognized%20within%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage%2C%20cannot%20but%20be%20said%20to%20be%20restricted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrom%20these%20three%20opinions%2C%20the%20following%20propositions%20emerge%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0first%2C%20a%20right%20external%20to%20the%20state%2C%20or%20having%20an%20origin%20that%20predates%20the%20state%2C%20cannot%20constitute%20a%20fundamental%20right%3B%C2%A0second%2C%20an%20unenumerated%20right%2C%20whose%20contents%20have%20been%20coloured%20by%20state%20action%2C%20cannot%20constitute%20a%20fundamental%20right%3B%20and%C2%A0third%2C%20a%20right%20attached%20with%20pre-existing%20religious%20or%20customary%20limitations%20cannot%20constitute%20a%20fundamental%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThree%20Standards%20of%20Apocryphal%20Origin%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0Assessing%20the%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Treatment%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Marry%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20imposition%20of%20such%20restrictions%20in%20elevating%20unenumerated%20rights%20to%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20it%20is%20submitted%2C%20are%20wholly%20unfounded%2C%20and%20are%20products%20of%20expediency%2C%20not%20constitutional%20doctrine.%20In%20no%20prior%20case%20has%20the%20court%20employed%20Justice%20Bhat%E2%80%99s%20tests%20assessing%20the%20temporal%20emergence%20of%20the%20impugned%20unenumerated%20right%20with%20the%20emergence%20of%20the%20state%2C%20or%20CJI%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20test%20of%20a%20right%20%E2%80%9Ccoloured%E2%80%9D%20by%20state%20action%20being%20ineligible%20to%20constitute%20a%20fundamental%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%E2%80%99s%20standard%20for%20elevating%20unenumerated%20rights%20to%20fundamental%20rights%20has%20been%20consistently%20liberal%2C%20for%20it%20has%20elevated%20unenumerated%20rights%20to%20this%20status%20regularly%2C%20even%20when%20the%20implications%20of%20such%20elevation%20are%20remotely%20foreseeable%20or%20make%20little%20conceptual%20sense.%3Cem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiaenvironmentportal.org.in%2Ffiles%2Fkudankulam%2520judgment.pdf%5C%22%3EG.%20Soundarajan%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%C2%A0for%20example%2C%20recognised%20the%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20development%E2%80%9D%2C%20achieved%20through%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20nuclear%20power%20plant%2C%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right%20(184)%3B%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F57050385%2F%5C%22%3EAssociation%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0read%20the%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20know%E2%80%9D%20into%20free%20expression%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20(%C2%B644)%3B%C2%A0%3Cem%3EUnni%20Krishnan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20as%20stated%20above%2C%20recognised%20the%20right%20to%20education%20under%20Article%2021%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1747577%2F%5C%22%3ESatwant%20Singh%20v.%20Passport%20Officer%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Erecognised%20the%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20travel%20abroad%E2%80%9D%20under%20Article%2021%20(%C2%B657)%3B%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2020%2F2418%2F2418_2020_36_1501_24294_Judgement_07-Oct-2020.pdf%5C%22%3EAmit%20Sahni%20v.%20Commisioner%20of%20Police%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20recognised%20a%20general%20%E2%80%9Cright%20of%20commuters%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right%2C%20which%20trumped%20protestors%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20assemble%20peacefully%20under%20Article%2019(1)(b)%20(%C2%B619)%3B%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1949293%2F%5C%22%3ER.L.E.K.%20v.%20State%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%93%20along%20with%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1813295%2F%5C%22%3Eslew%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20environmental%20litigation%20judgments%20%E2%80%93%20has%20recognised%20a%20general%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20clean%20and%20healthy%20environment%E2%80%9D%20under%20Article%2021%3B%20and%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2015%2F1458%2F1458_2015_3_1501_42634_Judgement_02-Mar-2023.pdf%5C%22%3EAnoop%20Banarwal%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Justice%20Rastogi%20has%20recognised%20the%20right%20to%20vote%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right%20%E2%80%9Cflow%5Bing%5D%20through%20Article%5Bs%5D%2015%2C%2017%2C%2019%2C%2021%E2%80%9D%20(%C2%B668).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETravel%2C%20education%2C%20commutation%2C%20and%20the%20environment%2C%20it%20is%20submitted%2C%20are%20external%20to%20the%20state%2C%20and%20predate%20the%20state%20%E2%80%93%20but%20have%20still%20been%20conferred%20with%20a%20fundamental%20right%20status.%20Further%2C%20CJI%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20test%20of%20a%20prior%20colouring%20of%20the%20impugned%20unenumerated%20right%2C%20if%20applied%20to%20the%20above%20cases%2C%20would%20mean%20that%20neither%20the%20right%20to%20education%2C%20nor%20the%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20know%E2%80%9D%20would%20be%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20for%20both%20Unni%20Krishnan%C2%A0(%C2%B686-90)%20and%C2%A0ADR%20(%C2%B67%2C%209-10)%20extensively%20document%20the%20role%20of%20state%20agencies%20in%20materialising%20these%20imperatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20now%20address%20the%20judgement%20of%20Justice%20Narasimha%2C%20which%20proposes%20that%20a%20right%20substantially%20intertwined%20with%20religious%20and%20customary%20restrictions%20cannot%20be%20deemed%20fundamental.%20He%20notes%20that%20legislation%20governing%20marriage%20%E2%80%93%20both%20religious%20enactments%20and%20the%20SMA%20%E2%80%93%20save%20uncodified%20religious%20custom%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20imposes%20many%20restrictions%20on%20marriage%20(%C2%B67-12).%20This%20conceptualisation%2C%20it%20is%20submitted%2C%20is%20regressive%2C%20and%20marks%20a%20setback%20in%20the%20judicial%20pursuit%20of%20democratising%20the%20%E2%80%9Cprivate%20sphere%E2%80%9D.%20The%20architecture%20of%20personal%20laws%20in%20India%20is%20such%20that%20it%20enables%20the%20coexistence%20of%20religious%20custom%20alongside%20many%20legislative%20and%20judicial%20modifications.%20Laws%20governing%20marriage%20and%20permitting%20custom%20are%20of%20the%20kind%20that%20they%20legislatively%20entrench%20custom%C2%A0as%20the%20decision-making%20rule%20to%20decide%20particular%20outcomes%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1883337%2F%5C%22%3ESection%206(3)%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20Hindu%20Succession%20Act%2C%201956%20requires%20classical%20Hindu%20law%20to%20be%20followed%20to%20determine%20coparcenary%20shares%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F635068%2F%5C%22%3ESection%205%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201955%20(%E2%80%9CHMA%E2%80%9D)%20permits%20the%20existence%20of%20legislatively-prohibited%20but%20customarily-accepted%20marriages.%20The%20situation%20envisioned%20u%2Fs%205%20of%20the%20HMA%2C%20Justice%20Narasimha%20notes%2C%20is%20similarly%20present%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F2476%2F1%2Fa1936_____3.pdf%5C%22%3EParsi%20Marriage%20and%20Divorce%20Act%2C%201936%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F2186%2F1%2FA1872-15.pdf%5C%22%3EIndian%20Christian%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201872%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(%C2%B69).%20More%20importantly%2C%20he%20notes%20that%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F2303%2F1%2FA1937-26.pdf%5C%22%3EMuslim%20Personal%20Law%20(Shariat)%20Application%20Act%2C%201937%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(%E2%80%9CShariat%20Act%E2%80%9D)%20also%20mandates%20the%20use%20of%20custom%20to%20decide%20norms%20of%20marriage%20(%C2%B69).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F115701246%2F%5C%22%3EShayara%20Bano%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Justices%20Nariman%20and%20Lalit%20have%20noted%20the%20Shariat%20Act%2C%20which%20also%20saved%20the%20application%20of%20uncodified%20Muslim%20law%20to%20mattes%20of%20divorce%2C%20caused%20the%20conferral%20of%20a%20statutory%20status%20to%20such%20custom%2C%20for%20the%20state%20authorized%20the%20use%20of%20custom%20as%20the%20sole%20%E2%80%9Crule%20of%20decision%E2%80%9D%20(%C2%B647-8).%20This%20meant%20that%20was%20no%20appreciable%20difference%20between%20a%20piece%20of%20legislation%20prescribing%20norms%20for%20divorce%20itself%2C%20and%20a%20legislation%20authorising%20custom%20to%20make%20the%20final%20call.%20Custom%20for%20marriage%2C%20akin%20to%20custom%20for%20divorce%2C%20must%20be%20treated%20as%20statute%20its%20application%20is%20secured%20solely%20by%20the%20latter.%20The%20persistence%20of%20custom%20in%20matters%20of%20marriage%2C%20therefore%2C%20cannot%20serve%20as%20a%20justification%20per%20se%20to%20deny%20marriage%20the%20status%20of%20a%20fundamental%20right.%20Further%2C%20the%20principle%20saving%20uncodified%20personal%20law%20from%20fundamental%20rights%20challenges%2C%20laid%20down%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F54613%2F%5C%22%3ENarasu%20Appa%20Mali%20v.%20State%20of%20Bombay%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20been%20referred%20for%20reconsideration%20in%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F163639357%2F%5C%22%3EIndian%20Young%20Lawywers%E2%80%99%20Association%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20indicating%20that%20its%20limited%20constitutional%20immunity%20might%20not%20even%20be%20long%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20brings%20us%20to%20the%20argument%20of%20Justice%20Narasimha%20that%20remains%20%E2%80%93%20marriage%20is%20ab-initio%20%E2%80%9Crestricted%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20by%20custom%20or%20otherwise%2C%20preventing%20its%20elevation%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right.%20Two%20objections%20may%20be%20laid%20to%20this%20%E2%80%93%20first%2C%20like%20the%20tests%20on%20elevation%20propounded%20by%20Justice%20Bhat%20and%20CJI%20Chandrachud%2C%20this%20test%20is%20also%20of%20apocryphal%20origin%2C%20never%20having%20been%20invoked%20prior%3B%20and%20second%2C%20it%20presumes%2C%20without%20justification%2C%20that%20an%20entitlement%20existing%20alongside%20restrictions%20cannot%20constitute%20a%20right.%20On%20the%20second%20objection%2C%20it%20must%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20nature%20of%20rights%20is%20such%20that%20they%20materialise%20with%20numerous%20limitations%2C%20and%20an%20approach%20denying%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20right%20based%20on%20its%20presently%20limited%20materialisation%20risks%20perpetually%20entrenching%20the%20status%20quo.%20This%20approach%2C%20effectively%2C%20is%20contrary%20to%20CJI%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%93%20while%20he%20states%20that%20an%20entitlement%20cannot%20constitute%20a%20right%20if%20its%20contents%20possess%20an%20origin%20external%20to%20the%20constitution%2C%20Justice%20Narasimha%20standard%20assesses%20only%20the%20entitlement%E2%80%99s%20contemporary%20operationalisation%2C%20which%20%E2%80%93%20if%20found%20riddled%20with%20obstacles%20%E2%80%93%20negates%20its%20claim%20to%20a%20right.%20Further%2C%20in%20case%20this%20standard%20were%20to%20be%20adopted%2C%20it%20would%20be%20hard%20to%20justify%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20right%20to%20privacy%20in%20the%20dawn%20of%20widespread%20surveillance%2C%20or%20a%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20clean%20and%20healthy%20environment%E2%80%9D%20in%20cities%20that%20are%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20polluted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Right%20to%20Marry%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0Does%20it%20Matter%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20of%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20right%20to%20marry%2C%20however%2C%20is%20a%20red%20herring.%20The%20existence%20of%20a%20specific%20unenumerated%20right%20need%20not%20be%20demonstrated%20by%20a%20petitioner%20when%20they%20experience%20a%20violation%20of%20their%20dignity%2C%20privacy%20or%20autonomy.%20The%20question%2C%20instead%2C%20is%20whether%20the%20present%20state%20action%20(which%2C%20in%20our%20case%2C%20is%20Section%204%20of%20the%20SMA%2FFMA)%20is%20such%20that%20it%C2%A0infringes%C2%A0a%20pre-existing%20fundamental%20right%20of%20the%20petitioner%2C%20and%20not%20whether%20the%20petitioner%20has%20a%20right%20to%20exactly%20what%20the%20state%20action%20prohibits.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20if%20state%20action%20prohibits%20activity%20%E2%80%9CX%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20puts%20the%20petitioner%20on%20a%20disadvantage%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20dignity%20or%20privacy%2C%20the%20question%20is%20not%20whether%20the%20petitioner%20has%20a%20right%20to%20do%20exactly%20%E2%80%9CX%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20only%20whether%20the%20impugned%20state%20action%20infringes%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20general%20fundamental%20right%20to%20dignity%20or%20privacy%20under%20Article%2021.%20Once%20this%20basic%20minimum%20task%20has%20been%20fulfilled%20by%20the%20petitioner%2C%20the%20burden%20shifts%20on%20the%20state%20to%20justify%20its%20restriction%2C%20which%20it%20may%20do%20in%20accordance%20with%20principles%20of%20proportionality.%20In%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2020%2F23817%2F23817_2020_34_1501_31829_Judgement_06-Dec-2021.pdf%5C%22%3EAkshay%20Patel%20v.%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20petitioner%20did%20not%20have%20to%20show%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20specific%20right%20to%20sell%20PPE%20kits%20under%20Article%2021%2C%20showing%20only%20an%20infringement%20thereof%20in%20light%20of%20state%20action%20regulating%20such%20sale%20(%C2%B629)%3B%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F17021567%2F%5C%22%3ERe%3A%20Ramlila%20Maidan%20Incident%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20petitioners%20only%20showed%20an%20infringement%20of%20their%20personal%20liberty%20due%20to%20state%20action%20evicting%20persons%20sleeping%20peacefully%2C%20not%20having%20to%20show%20how%20the%20constitution%20guarantees%20an%20explicit%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20sleep%E2%80%9D%20(%C2%B638)%3B%20in%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F850821%2F%5C%22%3EState%20of%20Maharashtra%20vs%20Prabhakar%20Pandurang%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20petitioner%20detenu%20only%20showed%20how%20state%20action%20preventing%20him%20from%20sending%20a%20book%20outside%20prison%20infringed%20his%20personal%20liberty%2C%20not%20having%20to%20show%20how%20a%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20write%20a%20book%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20fundamental%20right%20(%C2%B68)%3B%20and%20in%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F78536%2F%5C%22%3EFrancis%20Coralie%20Mullin%20v.%20Administrator%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20court%20noted%20that%20a%20meeting%20one%E2%80%99s%20lawyers%20and%20family%20while%20in%20prison%20would%20also%20constitute%20a%20fundamental%20right%2C%20not%20imposing%20the%20burden%20to%20show%20its%20existence%20on%20the%20petitioner%20(%C2%B68).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%2C%20however%2C%20about%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%20whose%20existence%20has%20been%20debated%20by%20a%20long%20line%20of%20cases%3F%20I%20submit%20that%20case-law%20dedicated%20to%20hollowing%20the%20scope%20of%20a%20right%2C%20instead%20of%20examining%20the%20validity%20of%20state-imposed%20restrictions%2C%20is%20largely%20disingenuous%2C%20and%20enters%20this%20discussion%20primarily%20in%20pursuit%20of%20justifying%20state%20action%20by%C2%A0negating%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20right.%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1306519%2F%5C%22%3EM.P.%20Sharma%20v.%20Satish%20Chandra%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Edenied%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20right%20to%20privacy%20in%20order%20to%20buttress%20the%20validity%20of%20CrPC-conferred%20powers%20of%20search%2C%20and%20all%20ERP%20jurisprudence%20%E2%80%93%20whose%20epitome%20is%20found%20in%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1612501%2F%5C%22%3EAnanda%20Margis%20(II)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20seeks%20only%20to%C2%A0ease%C2%A0state%20intervention%20in%20religious%20affairs%20by%20mandating%20each%20petitioner%20to%20demonstrate%20their%20religion%E2%80%99s%20foreseeable%20dismantling%20without%20the%20impugned%20practice.%20In%20asking%20the%20petitioner%20to%20demonstrate%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20specific%20right%2C%20the%20Court%20turns%20the%20table%20of%20burdens%2C%20rejecting%20a%20challenge%20at%20its%20very%20inception%20by%20creatively%20crafting%20the%20right%E2%80%99s%20non-existence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20the%20Court%E2%80%99s%20discussion%20on%20the%20right%20to%20marry%20suffers%20from%20the%20same%20malaise%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0its%20denial%20thereof%20seems%20specifically%20designed%20to%20defeat%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20case%C2%A0even%C2%A0before%20it%20begins.%20Three%20judges%20develop%20novel%20standards%20to%20determine%20when%20unenumerated%20rights%20warrant%20elevation%20as%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20with%20the%20three%20standards%20%E2%80%93%20if%20applied%20to%20past%20doctrine%20%E2%80%93%20would%20likely%20result%20in%20the%20deletion%20of%20many%20rights%20already%20read%20into%20Article%2021.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20standards%20make%20little%20sense%20when%20applied%20inter-se%20%E2%80%93%20while%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20holds%20that%20an%20entitlement%20cannot%20constitute%20a%20fundamental%20right%20if%20its%20contents%20are%20coloured%20by%20%E2%80%9Cnon-constitutional%20factors%E2%80%9D%2C%20Justice%20Narasimha%20effectively%20requires%20the%20very%20same%20%E2%80%9Cnon-constitutional%20factors%E2%80%9D%20to%20enable%20a%20substantially%20unrestricted%20materialization%20of%20the%20entitlement.%20Further%2C%20Justice%20Bhat%E2%80%99s%20prohibition%20on%20a%20right%20preceding%20the%20state%20is%20equally%20suspicious%2C%20for%20many%20entitlements%2C%20as%20discussed%20above%2C%20have%20originated%20independent%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20basis%2C%20I%20submit%20that%20the%20reasoning%20offered%20in%20refusing%20to%20deem%20the%20right%20to%20marry%20fundamental%20is%20highly%20questionable%2C%20for%20the%20standards%20laid%20down%20have%20little%20basis%20in%20case-law%2C%20yielding%20contradictory%20results%20when%20applied%20to%20previously%20elevated%20entitlements.%20At%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20judgement%20lies%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20pursuit%20of%20institutional%20abstention%2C%20with%20such%20abstention%20being%20justified%20through%20a%20delegitimisation%20of%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20case%20%E2%80%93%20the%20first%20mode%20of%20which%20was%20denying%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20right%20to%20marry.%20This%20question%20itself%20was%20unnecessary%2C%20and%20designed%20as%20a%20red%20herring%20to%20further%20justify%20the%20continued%20violation%20of%20dignity%20of%20non-heterosexual%20persons.%20The%20message%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20that%20there%20exists%20no%20right%20for%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20to%20assert%2C%20obviating%20any%20discussion%20of%20its%20persistent%20violation.%20It%20also%20means%20that%20some%20violations%20of%20dignity%20are%20more%20valuable%20than%20others%2C%20for%20legal%20standards%20exist%2C%20or%20be%20created%20conveniently%2C%20to%20craft%20a%20denial%20of%20dignity%20as%20lawful.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKartik%20Kalra%20is%20a%20student%20at%20the%20National%20Law%20School%20of%20India%20University%2C%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%20the%20blog%20%3C%2Fem%3EIndian%20Constitutional%20Law%20and%20Philosophy%3Cem%3E.%20Read%20the%20original%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2023%2F10%2F21%2Fthe-supreme-courts-marriage-equality-judgment-i-on-the-right-to-marry-and-a-case-of-abstention-through-delegitimisation-guest-post%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697941811000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-marriage-equality-judgment-analysis%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Such%20a%20denial%20was%20achieved%20through%20the%20creation%20of%20three%20never-be